title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Add milk; beat well.
Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Pour in batter, then add fruit.
Bake in moderate oven (about 350°) until browned.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put all together in a baking dish, except cheese.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: zucchini tomato quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned vanilla pudding
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch. With a wire whisk, gradually stir in milk and egg until well blended. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Reduce heat to low and continue boiling 1 minute. Remove saucepan from heat. Stir in vanilla extract. Spoon into 4 dessert bowls. Refrigerate to serve cold.

title: christmas dough ornaments
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Add water a little at a time.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until dough is smooth and putty-like.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick and cut out shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° on a cookie sheet until brown or let air dry for 48 hours on a window screen.
Paint; spray with clear acrylic or brush with shellac.
Remember to make a small hole in ornament with a toothpick before baking to hang with a ribbon.

title: excelle's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly; add milk.
Mix sugar and flour together; add to egg mixture, beating well.
Add salt, dash of black pepper and melted margarine.
Add cooked and drained corn.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and stir once; continue cooking until set and lightly browned, about 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with 2 cups of crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pan coating
directions: Use for cakes and muffins.
Mix all ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Store covered in glass jar on pantry shelf.
Brush onto cake and muffin pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup with water.
Blend in mayonnaise and add other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole and refrigerate overnight. Bake the next day at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with French fried onions and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: grandmother's raisin raggedy ann's
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water and drain dry on a towel.
Cream butter and sugar well, add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring, raisins, coconut and nuts if desired.
Fold in cornflakes and drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: steak dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a large cookie sheet, place piece of heavy-duty foil.
Place steak on foil.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion and peas on top of steak.
Prepare soup mix as directed. Pour over steak and other ingredients.
On this, sprinkle salt and pepper.
Bring foil up over steak and vegetables and seal so liquid won't run out.
Place in oven and bake 2 hours.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: While rice is cooking, brown meat until crumbly.
Drain; add onion and cook until soft.
Remove from heat.
Mix A.1., tomato sauce, rice, salt and pepper.
Cut top from peppers.
Remove seeds and fill peppers with meat and rice mixture.
Place peppers in 10-inch skillet; add butter and water.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems finely.
Brush caps with melted butter.
Blend soft butter with garlic; add cheese and mix well.
Stir in wine, soy sauce and the finely chopped stems to make a paste.
Fill caps.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet. Broil 5 inches from heat for approximately 3 minutes.

title: florida keys red snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub fish lightly with oil and sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper.
Melt butter and saute onion, green pepper and scallions until onion is cooked.
Stir in breadcrumbs, parsley and toasted almonds, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Stuff the fish with mixture and tie with string.
Place the fish on a length of aluminum foil and cover with alternating, slightly overlapping, slices of tomato, onion, orange and lime. Bring up edges of foil and secure it envelope style.
Bake 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: little latin meatballs
directions: Remove stems and seeds from chilies; chop chilies (may use canned chilies).
Mix chilies, beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased oblong, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook uncovered in 400° oven until brown, approximately 20 minutes.
Place meatballs in chafing dish.
Pour salsa over meatballs.
Makes 36 (1-inch) meatballs.

title: chicken parmes-aahn!
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in shallow pan. Combine melted butter, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and mix well. Coat chicken pieces with butter mixture; then roll in crumbs. Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Pour remaining butter mixture over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for one hour, basting once or twice with pan dripping.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir the cream cheese until slightly softened.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except walnuts and paprika.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: easy fried pies
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle flour on waxed paper and roll out biscuits flat.
Add 1 tablespoon applesauce mixture on each biscuit and fold over.
With fork go around edges, so it will seal biscuits.
Drop into hot oil and brown on both sides.

title: oven rice
directions: Combine all into a 3-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
If you need to bake a little longer, do so and then fluff with a fork.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together the flour and salt and stir in.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in finely chopped nuts (3/4 cup).
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press center with spoon or thumb.
Bake until set, about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Place jelly in center.

title: stuffed shells - meat filled
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Drain and cool by placing shells on wax paper to keep from sticking.
Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Combine meat, eggs, bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese, onions, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: mary jane salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry jello.
Add drained fruit.
Blend well.

title: volcano potatoes
directions: Add beaten egg yolks to mashed potatoes, then add salt, parsley and milk; mix together.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mold into cones 3-inches high and place in a shallow baking dish.
Make a deep indentation in the top of each cone and fill with grated cheese sprinkled with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tallerine
directions: Boil noodles in salted water; drain.
Cook beef until gravy color.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Drain oil from mixture and mix with all other ingredients except catsup.
Place in casserole dish and cover with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: endives and ham au gratin
directions: Wash endive in cold water and drain.
Butter heavy skillet in which endive will fit in one layer.
Sprinkle pan with a little salt and arrange endive in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with lemon juice and add the 1/2 cup of water.
Cover tightly and cook 30 minutes.
Watch carefully that liquid does not boil away.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Place the ham slices on a flat surface.
Place on each slice a braised endive.
Roll the ham slices to enclose the endive.
Secure with a toothpick.

title: penuche chews
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In a large saucepan combine butter, brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Turn into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan or two 9 x 9 x 1-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut while warm.

title: ranch dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in Dutch oven; bring to boil and simmer 30 to 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, reserving 3 cups broth in Dutch oven.
Remove meat from bones and cut into pieces.
Add potatoes and carrots to broth and bring to boil; simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Add chicken, corn, tomato sauce and pepper; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: green pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and save liquid.
Drain peas and discard liquid.
Blend crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix mushroom soup with asparagus liquid.
Grate cheese. Using 1/2 of each make layers of peas, asparagus, cracker crumbs, liquid and cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: best ever blueberry muffins
directions: Rinse and drain berries; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients; add milk, eggs and margarine.
Mix well.
Fold in berries gently. Fill well-greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield:
24 muffins.
"Freeze some for later!"

title: fresh ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Beat ginger, butter and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Beat in flour mixture until just combined.
Chill at least 1 hour. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and then roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake until edges start to brown, about 15 minutes.
Centers will be slightly soft.
Let stand on cookie sheets 1 minute and remove to racks to cool completely.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg and seasoning; mix well.
Shape into small balls and brown in skillet.
Keep warm until ready to use.
Combine jelly and chili sauce in chafing dish.
Add meatballs.
Keep warm over low heat.
Additional seasonings may be used, if desired.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Stir in milk, then flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in greased and floured 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with crumb topping.

title: goo-goo's
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, milk and margarine. Mix together peanuts and marshmallows. Add to melted mixture. Line 9 x 13 inch pan with wax paper. Pour mixture in pan and cool in refrigerator. Peel wax paper off and cut into bars.

title: thin pancakes
directions: Blend in blender.
Let set for 10 minutes, then fry.

title: mardi gras punch
directions: Stir together concentrates and apple juice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add ice cubes and small scoops of sherbet (raspberry, orange or lemon-lime).

title: gingerbread sauce
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add boiling water; cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Cool somewhat and serve over gingerbread or white cake.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll dough flat; crumble sausage on dough.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap dough tightly with seam down.
Place in a buttered pan; spread a little butter on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great for light lunch with salad or as a bread with dinner.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in the bowl until coated evenly.
Empty potatoes into a shallow baking dish or roasting pan. Bake, stirring occasionally, about 40 minutes until tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese cake cheeseless
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put pineapple in blender with dry milk and sweetener.
Soften gelatine in pineapple juice or little water. Heat to dissolve.
Put in blender.
Add lemon juice and flavoring. Blend 1 or 2 minutes until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan. Refrigerate.
Divide in 1/4 = 1 milk and 1 1/4 fruits.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine in skillet until tender. Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit in large bowl.
Mix with flour.
Add nuts and coconut, mix well.
Add milk; stir.
Bake in angel food pan.
Pat down and smooth top.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack in pan.
Remove.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Cool. Serve.

title: neapolitan swirl cake
directions: Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Grease and flour pan.
Blend cake mix (reserve marble pouch), water, oil and eggs.
Reserve 2 cups of batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan.
Combine 1 cup of reserved batter and chopped cherries.
Spoon over yellow batter.
Blend remaining cup of batter, marble pouch and chocolate chips.
Spoon over cherry mixture.
Marble with knife in folding motion.
Bake at 350°. Cool in pan for 25 minutes, then remove and spoon glaze over cake while warm.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut into thin slices.
Saute carrots in oil in large skillet 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 3 minutes or until crisp tender. Combine cornstarch and remaining ingredients; stir into carrots. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Add tomato paste and sauce, seasonings and onion.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
In a large casserole dish, alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles, cheese and cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onions together; add green chilies, seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Tear part of tortillas into strips.
Line bottom of greased baking dish.
Pour half of meat filling over tortilla strips.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Repeat with rest of tortilla and meat mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and tear in bite size pieces.
Chill.
Cook bacon and reserve drippings.
Make dressing from first 7 ingredients and keep warm.
Toss salad with warm dressing.
Serve with bacon and egg garnish.
Makes 6 large salads.

title: icebox squares
directions: Add milk to other ingredients to moisten.
Chill several hours. Cut into squares.

title: jello delite
directions: *If you use strawberry jello, use 1 pound frozen strawberries.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat ingredients and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream and spread evenly into 2 pie crusts.
Place back in freezer.
Melt marshmallows and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Mix well.
When mixture has cooled to room temperature, spread it on top of frozen ice cream pies.
Add pecan pieces or whipped topping.
Place back in freezer for at least 2 hours before eating.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spray an 11 1/2-inch quiche pan with Pam or grease with butter (can also use a round casserole dish).
Cook (bake) for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into pie servings.
Will make 2 quiches.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except steak.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Pound steak.
Cut in serving size and place in roaster.
Cover with sauce.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: cheese roll
directions: Roll out Velveeta cheese (between wax paper) until it is about 18 x 7-inches.
Mix cream cheese and green chilies.
Add a little seasoned salt, if desired.

title: milky way wonder cake
directions: Melt
candy
bars and 1 stick of the butter in saucepan over very
low heat.
Beat remaining stick of butter and sugar in medium size
bowl
until
fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Mix flour with soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir
until
smooth.
Add
melted candy, mixing well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter in 9-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in
350° oven for one hour and 20 minutes or until cake
springs back when lightly touched with fingertips. Top will be
quite dark.
Cool
in
pan
on
wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Frost.

title: layered cauliflower
directions: Mix garlic powder and prepared mustard to one small carton sour cream.

title: basic vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well, adding sugar slowly.
Add next three ingredients, mixing well. Pour into ice cream canister and fill to line with half and half.
Freeze according to freezer manufacturer's directions.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Put pork chops in long casserole dish. Add 8 ounces water, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place potatoes and onion layers on top of dish.
Mix soup and water together and pour over potatoes and onions.
Add a little more salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Remove cover and brown top for a few minutes.

title: potato leek soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the parsley, onions, celery, leeks and bay leaf. Cover with wax paper and let cook or "sweat" 6 to 7 minutes. This helps release the flavors in the vegetables and soften them without browning. Add the potatoes and chicken broth. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft. Dissolve cornstarch in water. Stir into the pot and cook, stirring until mixture is slightly thickened. Add cream. Remove bay leaf; bring back to a gentle boil over medium heat, adding salt and pepper and nutmeg. Reduce heat and simmer an additional 5 minutes. Taste for seasonings and adjust if necessary. Makes 2 quarts.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: In large pot, saute onion, garlic and celery.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add chicken broth, water, onion soup mix and tomatoes. Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Add macaroni.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
You can also add Worcestershire sauce for added flavor.
When serving, sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: grilled beef tenderloin
directions: You will need a meat thermometer.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
The cake is done when it leaves the side of the pan.
Remove cake immediately.

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Sprinkle chives on top.

title: fish florentine(microwave)
directions: Microwave spinach in a 1 1/2-quart casserole for 5 to 6 minutes on High; drain.
Layer mushrooms and fish over spinach. Combine milk, flour, salt and tarragon, mixing well.
Add margarine.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High or until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour mixture over fish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover.
Microwave 7 to 10 minutes on High or until fish flakes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet for 5 to 10 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat 1 minute after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat 7 minutes.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into well-greased and sugared 10-inch tube pan (too much batter for Bundt pan).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: hot cider
directions: Put in crock-pot and let boil, then turn to low.

title: corn and potato chowder
directions: Cook onion until tender, stirring constantly.
Add water, potatoes, salt and pepper; bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in corn, milk and ham.
Make a paste with 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 cup water. Stir until smooth.
Add to mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 6 cups.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: In the evening butter Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 package pudding mix, cinnamon and nuts. Melt oleo. Add brown sugar and pour over the top.
Cover with aluminum foil and towel and let stand overnight.
In the morning, bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: no-bake peanut oat cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Put over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined sheet pan.
Let stand until firm and cold.
Store airtight.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Discard outer leaves from cabbage.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Put wedges into a kettle; cover with water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil until leaves pull away from head.
Drain leaves well.
Arrange cabbage in prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, salt, pepper and cheese.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Pour hot milk over ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle white cake mix over cherries.
Pour melted margarine over top. Sprinkle almonds over all.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
May appear runny.
Allow to cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pavlova(italian meringue dessert)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line baking sheet with brown paper.
Draw 9-inch circle.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar on low speed until they hold soft peaks.
Slowly beat in superfine sugar on medium speed and continue beating until whites hold stiff peaks. Beat in vinegar.
Using circle as a guide, spread the meringue on paper ??? around.
Make a thick rim around the edge about 3/4-inch higher than center.

title: peach pie
directions: Place 1 stick of oleo in an oblong dish and melt in oven.
Cut up about 6 peaches in a bowl and sweeten.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk and pour over butter.
Pour peaches on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jeanne's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Brown ground beef with onion, bell pepper and seasoning; drain.
Put half of cornbread mixture in pan.
Layer meat on top.
Layer cheese and jalapeno peppers and the remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: keepsake biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead into dough.
Shape or cut into biscuits.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Recipe from the 1890's. Biscuits will keep 1 to 2 weeks and travel well.

title: tuilles
directions: In a food processor, finely grate almonds and add flour. Blend well.
Add butter, milk and sugar; blend for 8 to 10 seconds, until a ball of dough forms.

title: broccoli ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and broccoli.
Add ham and set the 3 aside. Make a sauce with butter, flour, milk and cheese.
Add onion and mustard to sauce and fold in mayonnaise.
Mix macaroni, ham, broccoli and sauce together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add sauce, tomatoes and seasoning.
Add beans; simmer until bubbly.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: orange nut crisps
directions: Cream sugar and butter very well.
Work in flour, orange rind, lemon rind and egg yolk.
Work together thoroughly with hands. Make into 24 small balls.
Roll each in slightly beaten egg whites, then in chopped nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Mix soup with Miracle Whip.
Add all ingredients, except the dressing, by layering soup/water chestnuts/chicken/eggs.
Top with dressing, made up by the directions on box, and dot with bits of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead.
Serves 8.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Flatten each biscuit into 5-inch circle.
Press each into the bottom and up sides of a greased
muffin cup.

title: fritos chili casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Combine meat, beans, 1 cup Fritos and 3/4 cup cheese.
Spread in a 10 x 6-inch dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and spread sour cream over top.
Top with rest of cheese and Fritos.
Bake for approximately 10 minutes more.

title: fast fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add water and butter; blend. Add vanilla.
Frost tops and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: mrs. wierth's fruit punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and mint leaves; chill.
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Makes 75 (4 oz.) servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together brown sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks.
Put milk in double boiler and heat.
Pour mixture in milk.
Add butter the size of an egg and vanilla.
Cook until thick and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar for meringue.
Put on top of pie and brown lightly in 375° oven.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and rice; set aside.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Cook frozen broccoli.
Mix chicken, rice and broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers tossed in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: May add food coloring.

title: chocolate velvet sauce
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Boil until mixture spins a thread.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate; stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla and salt.
Slowly add evaporated milk; stir constantly.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: jewish bread
directions: Mix together in double broiler over hot water until
sugar dissolves.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vegetables and rice
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes or until rice is tender and moisture absorbed.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in dish.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add margarine (melted) and milk.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.

title: spicy pork with baby corn
directions: Partially freeze pork; cut on the bias into thin bite-size strips.
For sauce, stir together water, bean sauce, cornstarch and red pepper.
Set aside.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add cooking oil.
(Add more oil as necessary during cooking.) Stir-fry celery in hot oil about 3 minutes or until tender-crisp. Remove celery from the wok or skillet.
Add half of the pork to the hot wok or skillet.
Stir-fry about 3 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove pork.
Stir-fry remaining pork about 3 minutes. Return all pork to the wok or skillet.
Stir in corn.
Push mixture from center of the wok or skillet.
Stir sauce; add to center of the wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Return celery to the wok or skillet.
Stir ingredients together to coat with sauce.
Arrange tomatoes atop. Cover and cook for 1 minute.
Serve immediately over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Add mixture plus the egg to the mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can easily double recipe.

title: meringues
directions: Beat whites and salt until frothy.
Add sugar very gradually until batter is stiff.
Fold in chocolate.
Drop big teaspoonfuls onto brown paper bag on a cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cookies in; turn off heat.
Close oven.
Leave in 6 hours or overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until it falls from bones.
Cool and remove meat from bones, discarding all fat and skin.
Place in baking dish.
Have potatoes, carrots, and onion diced and cooked tender in small amount of salted water.
Add these and peas to meat.
Make a thick sauce of 2
Tbsp. flour and broth, using water from vegetable if there is not too much.
Canned biscuits may be used but they must be patted very thin or may be baked before adding them to the casserole.
Cover top of casserole with biscuits and heat thoroughly, 20 minutes or longer uncovered in a 350 degree oven.

title: chocolate cake(eggless, milkless and butterless)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Into a bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Beat until smooth and pour into pan. Bake in oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and top with frosting.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with 24 liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Serve plain or with fruit filling on top. Makes 24 servings.

title: old fashioned slick dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt; scald flour with broth and stir until all flour is absorbed.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into squares and drop into boiling broth; cook until tender clear through.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add milk and flour alternately, then flavoring.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers until coarsely ground.

title: puffed wheat candy
directions: Blend sugar, water and vinegar in a large saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes, then add corn syrup and butter.
Cook to soft crack or until a few drops in cold water becomes hard and brittle.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow topping.
Pour over 1/2 package of Puffed Wheat in a buttered 9-inch cake pan.
Cut in squares when cool.
Yields 16 squares.

title: turkey quick meal
directions: Heat beans, soup, chicken or turkey meat, mushrooms and sage*, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and jello.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: creamed celery and pecans
directions: Cut celery in 1/2-inch diagonal pieces.
Cover with water and boil until tender, about 15 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour and gradually add milk, stirring until it comes to a boil and thickens.
Stir in salt and celery.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with pecans and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: nonedible play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from pan and knead slightly almost immediately.
This dough will keep for several weeks if stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
It has an almost velvety feeling, very pleasing to children.

title: macaroni-tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain well. Mix together the macaroni, tuna, celery, onion and 2 chopped eggs. Mix together the Miracle Whip, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add this mixture to macaroni mixture and sprinkle with celery seed and pepper.
Stir well.
Top with sliced egg.
Chill overnight or several hours before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt together margarine stick and 2 squares chocolate.
Add sugar, flour and eggs.
Put in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake between 350° and 375° for 28 minutes.
Top with ice cream.

title: blender pop-up bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour in blender.
Blend for 1 minute.
Make a well in flour in bowl and pour in liquid.
Mix well with spoon.
Set aside in warm place and let rise 1 1/2 hours or double in size.
Grease 2 coffee cans and divide dough equally. Put plastic lids on and let rise until lids pop off, about 3/4 hour.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes in can.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Double or triple according to number of wings.
Marinate 8 hours, turning a few times.
Bake in shallow pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: doughnuts or rolls
directions: Mix sugar, lard, salt and boiling water. When mixture is lukewarm, fold in egg and yeast mixture. Add flour or just enough to make kneadable dough. Let rise 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and roll out. Cut and place on cookie sheet. Let rise another hour and a half. Cook until brown at 400°.
Doughnuts are made just like the rolls, except they are fried in deep fat and dipped in mixture of powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix broccoli, cottage cheese, onion, eggs (well beaten) and cornbread mix. Mix together. Pour melted oleo in and mix well. Pour in pan you melted oleo in. Cook 45 minutes at 375°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix together and pour in cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with favorite icing.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and confectioners sugar. Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread mixture over cooled cookie crust.

Arrange fruit over cream cheese. Then combine marmalade or jam with water; blend well, then spoon over fruit (fresh or canned drained and quartered pineapple slices, sliced strawberries, sliced bananas, 1/4 cup strawberry jam and 1 tablespoon water) or you can use any fruit combination you like.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together sugar and flour, add eggs.
Add vanilla, salt, milk, melted margarine and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until light brown and custard is set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, salt and sugar together (be sure the brown sugar is free from lumps).
Stir in egg.
Add peanut butter, stirring in well.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with soda. Add dry ingredients to first mixture, blending thoroughly.
Form dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork first in one direction, then at right angles to form a cross.
Bake for 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook over medium heat to 234° to 240° on candy thermometer, soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Beat until thickened and creamy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into 2 crusts and chill. Keep refrigerated.

title: easy sausage bake
directions: Grease large cookie or jelly roll pan.
Fry sausage and onion until brown; drain.
Mix baking mix and beer thoroughly.
Spread batter in pan.
Spread sauce carefully over batter; top with sausage and remaining ingredients.
Bake until crust is golden brown at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: creole potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and put them in a boiler.
Cover with water and add Tony's seasoning.
Boil until tender.
For potatoes to get better seasoned, punch holes in potatoes.
This lets the seasonings cook into potatoes.

title: single acting baking powder
directions: Garnishes can be delicious treats as well as being decorative. They do not require a lot of time to prepare and need not be expensive.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: In saucepan, cook spinach and onion according to spinach directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
Combine eggs, cheese, salad dressing, margarine and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Cover and chill until needed.
(At this point, puffs can be frozen for later use.)
To serve, place chilled or frozen puffs on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Chilled Puffs take about 12 to 15 minutes; frozen puffs take about 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
About 60.

title: overnight salad
directions: Tear up lettuce.
Place in bowl.
Chop all other ingredients, except bacon and tomatoes, and sprinkle on lettuce.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, fry bacon crisp and crumble; sprinkle over salad.
Cut tomatoes in wedges and place over top.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Brown onions in shortening.
Pour muffin batter into greased pie plate; spread onions over top.
Beat sour cream and egg together; pour over all.
Bake according to package directions for corn muffins.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Filling:
Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs, ground beef and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.

title: kasper cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
With hands, mold into balls the size of hickory nuts.
Place on pan, not too close together.
Make a dent in each one with index finger.
Fill with 1/4 teaspoon jelly.
Bake in a slow 300° oven until light tan.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat margarine in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches), until melted.
Mix in baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken.
Place chicken pieces, skin sides down in pan.
Bake uncovered in 425° oven 35 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake uncovered until done, about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook yellow cake mix as directed; cool.
Crumble a layer of cooked cake in a punch bowl.
Mix 1 large box of vanilla instant pudding.
Spread pudding over cake.
Spread crushed pineapple with juice over pudding.
Add another layer of crumbled cake.
Spread cherry pie filling over cake.
Layer Cool Whip over top.
Add chopped nuts over top.
Chill and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain meat.
Put back on stove.
Add bouillon; stir until dissolves.
Remove from fire; add flour, tomato sauce, eggs and cheese.
Mix all together; pour into pie crust.
Garnish with 1/4 tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed hamburger meat
directions: Tear up bread and also Swiss cheese.
Add bouquet garni.
Pour half of beaten egg into dressing of bread and cheese.
Mix well. To meat, add a good pinch of bouquet garni and half of beaten egg. Mix beef well, then divide into four patties, placing them on wax paper.
Next, divide dressing, after well mixed, into four balls. Work beef around each, placing in a baking dish.
Top all with mushroom soup and bake uncovered at 400° for about 1 hour.
Baste at least once.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough to fill medium size pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and pineapple juice until smooth.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Top with assorted fruits.
Add water to remaining pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add cornstarch and heat until thick.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in foil.
Salt and pepper each piece well. Add green pepper strips, potato slices and margarine on top of chicken and seal foil.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off fat.
Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into cupcake papers in muffin pan and freeze.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar first, then add sour cream and vanilla. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture in 2/3 cup boiling water.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups water for 20 minutes. Boil sugar in 7 cups water. Mix tea, water and sugar water together; let cool. Add rest of ingredients and freeze. Serve with 50-50 or 7-Up.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter the casserole dish.
Add green beans.
Spread out even, then put a layer of corn on top of beans.
Mix sour cream, onions, cheese and soup together and pour on top of corn.
Take a stack of Ritz crackers and roll out real fine.
Mix 1 stick of butter or margarine and spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on the package.
(If frozen, do not overcook.)
Drain off all liquid.
Stir in cheese while broccoli is hot.
Place in casserole dish.
(You do not need to butter dish.)
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Cover over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and spices. Add to creamed mixture. Beat well. Fold in raisins and oatmeal. Drop by teaspoonful on prepared sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until firm.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.
No sugar, lo-cal.
One cookie contains 63 calories.

title: lemon with blueberries
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold pop or soft drink and lemon peel; chill.
Whip gelatin mixture; top with blueberries.
Yield: 4 servings.
Calories 36.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: goodie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a fork in a bowl.
Beat your eggs with fork and add to your dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and pecans. Mix well.

title: easy family lasagna
directions: In medium skillet, brown sausage and onion.
Drain grease. Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
In a greased 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish, spoon in enough sauce mix to cover bottom of pan.
Then, layer 3 uncooked lasagna noodles, 1/3 of the Ricotta cheese, 1/3 of sauce and 1/3 Parmesan cheese. Repeat two more times for a total of 3 layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or up to 24 hours.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Form ball.
Roll over pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: my favorite soup
directions: Brown meat until pink is gone.
Add water; bring to a boil. Add rest of ingredients; cook 1 hour.

title: cucumber cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add vinegar and onion.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into 6 individual molds and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold on greens and top with a dollop of mayonnaise.
Serves 6.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish or pan, layer the Doritos, then the chopped chicken.
Mix soups, green chilies, tomatoes and onion. Pour mixture over chicken and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until hot.
Serve with jalapeno jelly, green salad and extra chips.
Serves 8.

title: bean salad
directions: Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and salt, mix well.
Brown in a small amount of Crisco or butter.
Turn once.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll on floured board until 1/3-inch thick.
Cut in 1/2-inch strips.
If strips are too long, cut them into shorter lengths that are easy to pick up.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 12 minutes, but watch carefully.

title: port cobbler
directions: Dissolve sugar in lemon juice in bottom of tall glass.
Add wine and fill with ice and stir.
Garnish with orange slice and serve with a straw.
Makes 1 serving.
Increase by ten to make 1 quart.

title: apple and walnut salad
directions: Quarter and core the apples, but do not pare them.
Then dice them neatly and put in a bowl.
Add lemon juice and toss well to prevent discoloration.

title: raisin-nut spread
directions: Beat egg well.
Add sugar and juice of lemon.
Cook on top of double boiler until it begins to thicken.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter the size of small egg.
Let cool. Add nuts, raisins and mayonnaise.
Use with crackers or make small party sandwiches.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts as for pie crust.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool!!
Whip sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over baked, cooled crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Let stand for a few minutes to thicken.
Spread on top of second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of lemon mix and sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight!!

title: crumble topping for pies
directions: Blend together and put on top of pie.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and almond extract. Add flour, cream of tartar and baking soda. Chill 2 to 3 hours. Roll out dough very thin onto floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes. Do not overbrown. May frost with icing or leave plain.

title: stephen's salad dressing
directions: Mix all together in a jar with a lid.
Shake up very well.

title: christmas nut thins
directions: Blend sugar and butter together.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift in flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Add flavoring; mix until smooth and light.
Drop onto greased baking sheet; spread well apart.
Place half nut meat in center of each cookie.
Place and bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, vanilla and oil.
Pour egg mixture over flour mixture and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Turn into two greased loaf pans or one 12 x 6-inch disposable pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Cut in butter.
Mix egg and milk; add to other ingredients.
Knead for a few minutes. Put in well buttered 8-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Serve with lots of strawberries.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Chill several hours for ease in handling.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Roll balls while still warm in confectioners sugar.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak with onion and butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: spinach dip
directions: Place spinach on paper towel and press between sheets or squeeze to absorb as much of the moisture as possible. Combine spinach with remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill mixture several hours. Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: barbecued rice
directions: Cook celery and onion in chicken broth until tender (broth will cook down low).
Add chicken soup and liquid smoke and stir. Melt 1 stick of butter in casserole dish and pour over rice; mix with other ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: won ton cinnamon crisps
directions: Cut each won ton in 1/2 to make 2 rectangles. If using eggroll skins, cut each into 1/4 then cut each into 8 rectangles from each skin. Brush some butter on bottom of 10' x 15' baking pan. Place into pan close together. Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rectangles.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand together overnight.
In the morning, boil 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the Jell-O. Mix and put in jars.

title: chess pie(nancy's grandmother's recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except vanilla extract.
Then add vanilla extract and pour into unbaked crust.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Put pie in oven, then reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, beating well. Combine flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture along with bananas, vanilla and pecans, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Brown bacon and cook until transparent, but not crisp.
Drain. Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper or seasoning salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese.
Just before serving, add sour cream and heat to warm up the sour cream.

title: chess cake
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in eggs with mixer, one at a time. Sift powdered sugar in mixture and pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cake should be golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone it. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Take chicken and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Add spaghetti. Add sauteed onion and bell pepper. Mix soups with 1/2 can of water and mix in casserole. Add Ro-Tel and top with lots of Velveeta. Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding.
Crumble cooled, baked cake into glass bowl. Layer half of cake crumbs and top with half of pie filling, pudding, drained pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers. Chill overnight.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil until tender, 1 large hen or fryer, debone chicken and save broth.
Simmer in skillet with 3 tablespoons salad oil, chopped onion and green pepper; add can of Ro-Tel (tomatoes and chilies), chili powder, cumin, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Separately mix together cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup and broth; add this to the sauce and mix well.

title: peach salad
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish with mayonnaise. Bring to boil the crushed pineapple and juice.
Add 2 small peach jello.
Simmer this until jello has melted. Take off stove and let cool.
When mixture has cooled, add buttermilk, Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Pour into dish and refrigerate.

title: tex-mex-tamale casserole
directions: Grease large 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Spread corn in pan. Top with onion, then chili and tamales.
Top with cheese as last layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and bubbling.
Serves 6 people.

title: chocolate layer pie
directions: Mix together melted margarine, nuts, flour and powdered sugar. Press into large pie dish or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: company salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
When gelatin begins to congeal, add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 9-inch glass square dish and refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; mix with sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and butter. Pour in greased casserole dish.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Spray baking sheet with three coats vegetable coating spray. Remove skin from chicken.
Combine bread crumbs, flour and seasonings in large plastic bag.
Shake to mix well.
Roll chicken pieces in yogurt.
Place in bag and shake to coat.
Remove to baking sheet.
Spray chicken with vegetable coating.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Turn every 20 minutes to allow even browning.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and season with salt, pepper and spices to taste.
Roll into golf ball size meatballs. Brown, then add soup and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with baked potatoes.
Gravy very good on potatoes.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers.
Leave syrup on cucumbers for a few minutes, then pour back over cucumbers and seal.
If you wish, you may add 1 clove of garlic to a quart.
Some add 1/3 teaspoon mustard seed and garlic to a quart.

title: spinach salad
directions: Arrange bacon, eggs, scallions and
croutons
over spinach. Combine all other ingredients and mix
well.
Pour	over spinach when ready to serve.

title: snickers bar pie
directions: Soften ice cream in a large bowl.
Sprinkle pudding mix over ice cream and mix.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip, stirring to blend well.
Spoon into a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Freeze.

title: microwave chili beans
directions: Crumble hamburger in a 3-quart casserole bowl.
Stir in onion. Cook at High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Stir once; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered with lid, at High for 6 to 7 minutes and at Medium-low for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir; let stand, covered, 7 minutes before serving.

title: spice and applesauce cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Split rolls.
Place bottom of rolls in Pyrex dish.
Place ham and cheese on roll.
Replace top of rolls.
Melt butter.
Stir in with mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on rolls.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in oven until rolls are brown and cheese is melted.

title: cheddar cabbage wedges
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
order listed. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Place beans, pork, water, onion, garlic, seasonings and green chiles in a heavy kettle.
Cook until thick.
Serve over corn chips.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk and basil.
Add tortellini, green pepper, red pepper, garlic and olives.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and chill.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Add all ingredients.
Cook on low heat.
Serve with corn chips.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix the 2 dressings together.
Mix with all other ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss together.
When ready to serve, add Catalina dressing.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly with hands.
Form into small bite size balls.
Freeze until firm and bake as needed in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve warm.

title: company squash
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add margarine, sugar, egg, mayonnaise and other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in a jar.
Store in icebox for 24 hours. Then eat.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2)
directions: In big bowl, mix lemon juice and milk together.
Add pineapple and cut up oranges.
Mix; fold in Cool Whip.
Put in shells. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: spicy pumpkin bars
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Stir together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, frost with Spice Frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Serve on salad greens, if desired.

title: louisiana methodist punch(arkansans may try this also.)
directions: Add all ingredients in gallon container.
Fill with water and chill.

title: chicken francaise with broccoli
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Flour very thin chicken cutlets and add to eggs.
Heat oil in saute pan until hot.
Cook chicken until golden brown.

title: by-cracky bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in the vanilla. Place 1/3 of batter in another bowl and add unsweetened chocolate and walnuts to this mixture.
Spread chocolate and mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange 8 to 9 double graham crackers over batter.
Add chocolate morsels to remaining 2/3 batter and drop by spoonfuls over graham crackers.
Spread batter to cover.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars. Yields 3 dozen.

title: blueberry or cherry dessert
directions: Mix together with fingers graham crackers, powdered sugar and margarine/butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan for crust. Combine eggs, granulated sugar and cream cheese.
Spread filling over crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool a bit.
Spread Comstock (complete) blueberry or cherry pie filling over the top. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Great on grilled steaks.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt and cool unsweetened chocolate and margarine.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add chocolate and margarine; beat again.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add flour, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Pour and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Saute onion in butter.
Layer carrots, onion and slices of cheese in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: beef carbonades(serves 6)
directions: In pan, brown meat in oil.
Remove.
Brown onions and garlic about 10 minutes in pan.
In casserole dish, alternately layer meat and onions.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat layers, adding some parsley sprigs.
In pan, combine stock (plus any meat juice), brown sugar, parsley, vinegar, bay leaf, thyme and flour.
Return to stove.
Add beer and bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over meat and onions in casserole dish.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with parsley potatoes or boiled noodles.

title: cheese pie
directions: Let cheese soften, then put in mixer.
Cream the cheese and add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Bake in large greased deep pie pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: queen's biscuits
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Gradually add 1/2 milk and flavoring.
Blend well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together in a bowl.
Make a hollow in center of dry ingredients and gradually blend in sugar mixture.
Mix until liquid is absorbed. If too dry, gradually add remaining milk to make soft, manageable dough.
Mix lightly.
Pat into a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate 1/2 hour or more.

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the ground chuck, egg, soup mix, salt and pepper together.
Roll into meatballs.
Cook in oven until done.
Drain off fat.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour cheese on top of meatballs.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the cheese.
Put back into oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Eat as a side dish or for sandwiches.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Crumble up corn bread and biscuits. Pour melted butter over bread. Add onions, salt and pepper.
Add broth from boiled chicken.
Mix well. Add eggs and cream of chicken soup.

Mix well. Pour 1/2 of mixture in large pan. Spread chicken, that has been deboned, over dressing mixture in pan. Top chicken with remaining dressing mixture. Cut chips of butter over top of dressing. Bake in preheated 400 degree over. Watch for bubbling in middle of dressing and then let brown.

title: crisp winter slaw
directions: Combine salt, vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Chill. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients and drain fat.
Add tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Layer in baking dish starting with meat mixture, then tortillas. End with meat mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 F for 35 minutes.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed;
bake in 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Cool cake completely, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve one
cup of	sour
cream
for
frosting.
Spread remainder of mixture between layers of cake.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef with bacon.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add seasonings to meat mixture.
Stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot poppy seed noodles.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown seasoned and floured chops.
Place in a baking dish; cover with dry rice.
Mix soup with milk; pour over rice, being sure rice is completely covered with liquid.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: white cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add dates, raisins and nuts if desired.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch.
Bake in 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
When cooked, even the bottoms should still be white (don't brown them).

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate cheese and mix with rest of ingredients, using hands. Shape in a roll or ball and roll in paprika.
Wrap and chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add cooked macaroni and drain. Mix cream of chicken soup, hamburger and macaroni together.
Add cheese on top.
Cook in the oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Slice celery and green onions.
Brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Drain.
Slice mushrooms and water chestnuts in 1/2.
Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over Chinese noodles or cooked rice.

title: ole timey scotch aigs
directions: Hard boil 5 to 6 aigs; shell.

title: corn dog casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute celery in margarine for 5 minutes.	Add onions; saute for 5 minutes.
Place in a large bowl; set aside. Cut hot dogs lengthwise into quarters, then cut into thirds.
In the same skillet, saute the hot dogs for 5 minutes or until lightly browned; add to vegetables.
Set aside 1 cup.
In a large bowl, combine milk, eggs and pepper.
Stir in cornbread mixes. Add the remaining hot dog mixture.	Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.	Spread into a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Top with reserved hot dog mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Have ready slightly beaten eggs.
Mix first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over direct heat 5 to 7 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs slowly to hot mixture. Continue cooking until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into a prebaked 8-inch pie crust.
Cover; chill in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.
Arrange semi-sweet chocolate pieces on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and add Italian dressing to taste.
Salt and pepper.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry beef, peppers, onions and celery until beef is browned. Add Worcestershire, catsup, vinegar, sugar and tomato sauce on low heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: italian string beans
directions: Steam beans in salted water, according to package directions. Cook until they are crisp and very green, do not overcook.	When beans are about 3 minutes from being done, braise onions, parsley, basil, salt and pepper in a small frying pan with olive oil.
Drain beans and put into covered dish.
Immediately pour the onion mix over the beans.
Stir.
Cover and let stand for 3 minutes, then serve.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken (cut into small cubes).
Brown slightly.
Lower heat.
Add amount of sauce desired.
Cover and cook until tender, stirring occasionally. Serve over lettuce, tomatoes and chips.
Top with cheese, picante sauce and sour cream, if desired.

title: cabbage with sausage
directions: Chop cabbage and cook about 20 minutes.
Chop apples and add. Add sausage and remaining ingredients and cook another 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pizza
directions: Put pizza sauce on crust.
Add pepperoni and cheese. Put in the oven for 1 hour at 100°.
Take it out when done, put it in a box and take it home to eat.

title: butterscotch topping for ice cream
directions: Combine all the ingredients and simmer for 3 minutes.
Cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cut bread slices (5) into cubes into buttered dish.
Put 1/2 spinach over bread, then 1 cup cheese.
Repeat this again with remaining ingredients.
Pour beaten eggs into soup.
Stir well. Pour onto casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight for 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew(lapskaus)
directions: Peel and chop everything.
Cook until tender.
May be cooked in a crock-pot.
Serves 8.

title: easy party nachos
directions: Place a bowl of salsa in the center of a large round platter. Arrange chips around bowl.
Sprinkle peppers, tomatoes, and olives on chips.
Pour warmed cheese sauce over the top.
Enjoy!

title: summer spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in a large bowl.
Add prepared tomatoes, cucumber, peppers, chickpeas and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serves approximately 16.

title: rocky road salad
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
When serving, sprinkle chips and nuts on top.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in can of chicken broth.
Add and cook butter, celery and onion and then add cream of celery soup and milk.

title: ellen barklow's ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, eggs, bread crumbs and milk; form loaf. Make dressing of vinegar, water, brown sugar and dry mustard. Pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Blend flour into melted shortening in heavy saucepan.
Add onions, garlic, green pepper and parsley.
Cook until light brown, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomatoes, thyme, red pepper, bay leaves, celery seed and salt.
Add shrimp.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 30 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: robert redford chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together the oleo, flour and chopped nuts.
Spread mixture in oblong pan; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: diet applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Drain well.
Add sauce, eggs, oil and sweetener to raisins.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well again.
Bake in a glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed until thick
and creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat constantly until very thick, 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in water and vanilla.

title: peanut butter soup
directions: Mix together chicken stock, onion and celery; simmer for about 1 hour.
Strain out onion and celery; discard.
Stir in peanut butter and dissolve.
Mix flour with remaining ingredients and simmer together 15 minutes.
If too thick, thin with milk. Garnish with bacon crumbs or minced country ham.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut meat into strips about 3 to 4 inches long and 1 inch wide. Melt shortening in skillet over moderately high heat (about 275°) and cook meat until lightly browned.
Drain pineapple and mix juice with the 3/4 cup water, the vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat (about 200°) 1 hour or until tender.
Combine cornstarch and the 2 tablespoons water.
Add to meat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks, onions and green pepper. Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes until vegetables are tender. Serve on rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Bring oleo and Coca-Cola to a boil. Pour over flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into large cake pan, preferably bigger than 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan.

title: broccoli salad with bacon
directions: Thaw petite broccoli florets in cold water; drain and place in mixing bowl.
Cook bacon in skillet or microwave until crisp. Crumble and add to broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter
and mix all ingredients together.	Pour in a pan and cool;
cut into squares.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in microwave. Cook on High for 3 minutes or until flexible.
Layer broccoli in a 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, mix soup, sour cream, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Stir in chicken cubes and
pour over broccoli. Set aside and melt butter in small bowl for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until hot.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan; stir in milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring to 234° (soft ball stage) or until small amount of syrup dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball.
Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses its gloss.
Quickly spread in prepared pan. Cool completely; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Sift flour twice and add to mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel dip for sliced apples
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve room temperature with thinly sliced apples.
I prefer Granny Smith apples.
If you don't want the apples to turn brown, put a little lemon juice on them.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat together ingredients and shape into rolls.
Chill overnight.
Cut into slices (1/8-inch). Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until brown.

title: rum cake
directions: Cover bottom of a greased and floured Bundt pan with nuts.
Mix cake ingredients in order named and pour over nuts in pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, gelatin, egg yolks, milk, pumpkin and spices and beat together. Use very low heat or a double boiler.
Stir constantly for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool until mixture begins to gel.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon of cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Beat 3 tablespoons of sugar in gradually until whites are stiff and glossy.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.

title: pork 'n crescent pasties(easy, fast and great)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook green pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in pork, ginger, salt, applesauce and mustard; set aside.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon about 1/3 cup meat mixture on one end of each rectangle.
Fold dough in half over filling.
Press edges to seal.
Brush each with egg.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan; press around sides and bottom.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put on any type cracker.
I find low-fat Nabisco Harvest Crisp the best.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flavoring.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour gradually with sour cream to the creamy mixture.
Eggs should be at room temperature.
Preheat oven.
Bake at 325° in tube pan, 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Pour buttermilk over oats in a medium bowl; let stand about 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can prepare ahead and freeze.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar,
salt and baking powder.
Melt shortening and add to
dry
ingredients.
Stir
well
and
allow to cool. Add eggs, one at
a
time,
mixing
well.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingrediens in a large salad bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add flour and soda (sifted), sour cream and whole eggs (one at a time).
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until done (approximately 1 hour).

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:	Melt
margarine;
pour	into flour and powdered sugar. Spread on	buttered
pizza pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Place half hot dog and half slice cheese on dough and roll up.
Place on baking sheet lined with foil.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
(Rolls will be browned.)

title: hawaiian candy
directions: Combine sugars, cream, butter and ginger.
Boil to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm; add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add pineapple and nuts; spread on oiled surface to harden.

title: small apple cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Add all other ingredients. Bake in 8-inch pan or angel food pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy golden glazed chicken
directions: Coat chicken with first 3 ingredients.
Place in well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, 30 minutes.
In small saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in preserves and bouillon; heat until bouillon dissolves.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon onion/preserve mix over chicken and bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nutty broccoli and rice
directions: Divide broccoli and rice evenly into 4 pint-size Ziploc microwave bags.
Mix remaining ingredients and divide evenly into the 4 bags.
Seal bags and shake well.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to use.
To cook from freezer, make 1-inch center vent in each bag.
Microwave each bag 2 minutes on Defrost.
Cook on Full power 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, shaking once during cooking. To cook from refrigerator, simply omit Defrost step.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic and salt and saut 2 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple layer cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in lemon juice and flavorings.
Pour in 3 cake pans.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, one cup at a time.
Form into small balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: dilly of a dip(3 cups)
directions: Blend cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Mix well and chill in bowl to be used to serve dip. Sprinkle paprika lightly.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant pulp in salted water (keep shells for stuffing, if desired).
Saute onion in butter.
Add shrimp and crab meat and season to taste.
Soak bread and crumble.
When mixture is cooked and bread crumbled, stuff into shells.
Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Heat in 350° oven until brown.
Serves 12.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pack in 10 x 6-inch pan (greased bottom) the graham cracker crumbs and oleo, melted (1 stick).
Whip until fluffy the powdered sugar, eggs and 1/4 pound oleo; spread over crumbs.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread over egg mixture.
Slice 3 large bananas next, to cover pineapple.
Spread on large Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put the spices in a small cloth bag and mix other ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes; do not boil.
When done simmering, remove the spices and cinnamon.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mince onion; saute in butter.
Brown meat in separate pan. Add seasoning.
Combine casserole, adding sour cream at this time. Cover and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: strawberry tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, orange juice and sugar until well blended. Divide mixture and spread over bottom of each tart shell.
Add strawberries and brush with orange marmalade.
Chill 1 hour; serve.

title: mom's modern meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan, except crackers. Knead well to blend flavors. Add crushed crackers, a little at a time, to allow flavors to soak into it. The texture should be firm, not dry. If too moist, add a few more crackers.
Mold into a Pyrex loaf pan. Lay 2 strips raw bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in hot oven.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl. Stir in milk and sugar to make batter.
Pour into hot baking dish. Spoon peaches over batter.
Pour juice evenly over all.
Bake 30 minutes or until batter has risen and is golden brown.
Serve hot with ice cream or dollop of sour cream.

title: mostaccioli with spinach and feta cheese
directions: Melt butter with 2 teaspoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add pine nuts and garlic; saute until pine nuts are light brown, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes and saute until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Place cooked pasta in serving bowl.
Add remaining oil to pasta and toss.
Pour spinach-pine nut mixture over and toss to coat.
Add Feta cheese. Season with salt and pepper and toss thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook meat, onions and bell peppers together and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: basil pesto
