directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in water. Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Pour half of the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set. Set the remaining gelatin mixture aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Add Cheez Whiz and undiluted soup.
Pour boiling water over broccoli to thaw and drain well.
Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: After chicken is done, take off skin and bones.
Cut in small pieces.
Rinse noodles and put everything in pot together. Season to taste.

title: mock chicken casserole
directions: Saute tacos, drain on paper towel.
In large bowl mix next 7 ingredients.
Break tacos into smaller pieces like potato chips. Cover bottom of casserole with broken tacos, spoon mixture over broken tacos.
Grate Mozzarella cheese over mixture, layer until all of mixture is used.
Top with grated American cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.
If you wish you can make casserole the day before and keep covered in refrigerator until baking time.
Remove lid to bake.

title: nuts for chocolate bars
directions: Mix flour and 1/2 cup of sugar in small bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of greased, foil-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until edges are lightly brown.
Microwave chocolate and remaining 1/4 cup margarine in large bowl on High 1 1/2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in corn syrup, remaining 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 30 minutes, or until filling is set.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small florets (approximately 2 cups each). In large bowl, toss all ingredients to mix. Serve at once or cover and refrigerate several hours. Can be kept 3 to 4 days in refrigerator. (Low calorie, 99 per cup.) Serves 8.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.

title: favorite cream pie filling
directions: Mix together in large saucepan, sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
(Can do in microwave on High power, stirring every 2 minutes.)
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Then blend this into the hot mixture in the saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together a day or so in advance.
Before serving, add dressing.

title: pecan waffles
directions: Measure and combine dry ingredients together. Mix oil with milk and eggs. Stir into dry ingredients. Mix until smooth. Add pecans and mix well. Makes 8.

title: french cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth, whisk in the whipping cream until smooth again. Add the sugar and mix well. Add the lemon juice and mix well. Pour into the cracker crust and chill for about 1 hour. Spoon the pie filling over the top. A ring of thick cream can be piped around the edge to make it a little more special, with the pie filling poured into the middle. Serve with extra whipped cream.

title: denny's goulash
directions: Saute beef and onion until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, kidney beans and mushrooms.
Cook macaroni; drain and add.
Parboil celery and green pepper 5 minutes and add. Season to taste.
Simmer gently until heated through.
Great reheated!

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Saute the onion and potato in butter or bacon drippings until tender.
Add zucchini and cook until tender, but not mushy.
Add the tomato and heat through.
Sprinkle with the cheese and heat until the cheese melts and coats the vegetables.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Squash and strain strawberries.
Mix the strawberry puree in a cocktail glass and add the fresh orange juice and a splash of whiskey.
Mix with ice cubes, shake thoroughly and pour into champagne glasses.
Serves 2.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together; put in casserole dish.
Top with Toasties or chips (crushed).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Mix and bake in a buttered bread loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Eat bread after it has cooled, it will be easier to slice at room temperature.

title: creole corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, cornmeal, onion, peppers (which have been seeded and chopped), salt and baking soda.

In another bowl, beat eggs, milk and oil. Add corn; mix well. Stir into the rice mixture until blended. Fold in cheese. Sprinkle a well-greased 10-inch ovenproof skillet with cornmeal. Pour batter into skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done. Cut into wedges while warm and serve.

title: oriental shish-kabob marinating sauce
directions: Mix well all of the above and use to marinate your meats before cooking or grilling.

title: pork roast
directions: Make small holes in roast and put garlic cloves inside.
Cover with onions.
Wrap in foil and cook on 350° for 3 hours.
Take foil off top until the grease cooks out.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done.
Loosely cover with foil for first 30 minutes.

title: microwave stuffing muffins
directions: In medium size, heat-resistant nonmetal bowl, melt the 1/2 cup butter on full power 1 minute.
Add onion, celery and mushrooms and heat, uncovered, on full power 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle sage over vegetable mixture.
Add chicken broth and stir to combine.
Heat, uncovered, on full power 3 minutes.
Add bread stuffing and toss lightly.
Lightly grease 8 small, heat resistant, nonmetallic custard or coffee cups with butter.
Divide stuffing among cups.
Just before serving, heat, uncovered, on full power 8 minutes or until heated through. Serves 8.

title: giant oatmeal cookies
directions: *Cover and soak in hot water for 20 to 30 minutes, then drain.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Slice onion and cut pepper in strips.
Layer in container (not metal).
Sprinkle with salt, black, pepper and celery seed.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread into an ovenproof serving dish. Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
It will be finished when peaks turn slightly brown.
Serve with complementary crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix well in blender.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan and bake until golden and set.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
For glass pie dish, bake at 325°.

title: sweet spaghetti
directions: Boil water and cook macaroni.
In another pot, brown onion and garlic in oil over low heat.
Then add chopped meat.
When cooked, add tomato paste, sauce and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil. Then simmer about 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain macaroni.
Pour sauce over macaroni and serve.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Cool to lukewarm; add vanilla.
Beat until candy loses its shiny state, then add cherries, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Spread in buttered dish; cut into squares.

title: chile calabazas(squash)
directions: Slice the squash in 3/16-inch thick slices (my, he's particular, Ed).
Slice the onion thinly as well as the pepper. Get all the white membrane out of the pepper before you slice it as this membrane is bitter.
Try to get long slices of the onion and pepper.
Cover the vegetables with water and add the chili and comino.
Simmer until all the vegetables are tender and taste before serving.

title: mexican cheese snacks
directions: Stir all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
After draining beef, add all cans (undrained) and envelopes to the beef in a large pot.
Let simmer for at least 30 minutes.
It works great in a crock pot.
Serves 6- 8. Kids love this recipe.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Blend and spread over salad; garnish with stuffed olives.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, brown beef; drain. Add onion and celery; cook until tender. Add water, beans, tomatoes, cabbage, chili powder and salt; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20-30 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Top each bowl with mashed potatoes if desired.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: Spread beans on a 10-inch platter.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Combine crackers, cheese, pimento, bell pepper, onion, salt and pepper. Add eggs, milk, butter and macaroni.
Pour into a buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: surprise brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix brownie mix, water and eggs.
Divide batter into 24 cupcake cups (approximately 2/3 full).

title: ham with pineapple sauce
directions: Place ham on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until ham is heated through.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine 1/4 cup water, brown sugar, soy sauce, ketchup, mustard and pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and remaining water until smooth; stir into pineapple sauce.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve with ham. Yield: 16 to 24 servings with 3 cups sauce.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Stir together milk and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.

title: hummus
directions: Add all ingredients to food processor.	Serve with pita bread. Lasts 3 days.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, 3/4 cup Rice Krispies, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix sugar, catsup, nutmeg and dry mustard.
Add half of this mixture to beef.
Form balls and place in Pyrex dish.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cereal on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Mix together jello, hot water and vinegar; mixing until dissolved.
Add olives and cherries.

title: gordon's hot peach pie
directions: First mix well the sugar and flour together in bowl, then adding only juice from peaches mix well together with sugar and flour mixture. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 10-inch baking dish. Pour into cooking dish, the peach mixture.

Crumble Ritz crackers on top of the peach mixture. Melt 1 stick butter and slowly drizzle over crumble Ritz crackers used as topping for the peach pie. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot or can be served cold. Delicious! Try it.

title: geraldine's special banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O boxes for pudding; add Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and shape into loaves.
Bake at 300° about 2 hours.

title: hungarian (kifli) cookie
directions: Mix well with hands. Roll into a ball, then pinch off about the size of a walnut into 50 balls and refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(servings: 6)
directions: You will need about 6 foot of cheesecloth.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust
with
graham crackers and 1 stick of margarine, melted.
Press
into
a
x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill. Beat eggs,
sticks soft margarine and powdered sugar for 15 minutes. Pour over graham cracker crust.
Layer pineapple and bananas. Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Place the cooked and drained ground round into a skillet.
Add water and all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for approximately 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook rice; drain.
Saute celery and onion in butter until tender and add to the drained broccoli.
Mix the 2 cans of soup and half and half cream with rice and 1/2 of the cheese.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle remainder of cheese over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yamisette casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until almost done.
Strain, brown meat with chopped onion.
Add tomato soup, vegetable soup and water.
Cook for 5 or 10 minutes, then add the macaroni.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs or grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully and drop into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° (approximately 45 minutes) until brown.

title: angel hair with special sauce
directions: Heat chicken broth in a medium saucepan. Add tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Add seasonings.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to boiling sauce to reach desired thickness.
Cook angel hair pasta according to package directions.
Drain but do not rinse. Serve with sauce.
Cooked meatballs may also be added to the sauce, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop onion and cook.
We prefer cooking on paper towel in the microwave oven until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: cherry cream cheese cupcakes
directions: In bottom of each cupcake liner in cupcake pan, place one vanilla wafer.
Mix all remaining ingredients except cherry filling.
Spoon mixture onto wafers.
Cool in refrigerator until set.
Top each with pie filling.
Keep refrigerated while storing.

title: super hero melt
directions: Cut bread in half crosswise; split each half horizontally. Layer the bottom of each bread half with salami, ham, bologna and both cheeses.
Place paper towel on paper plate.
Place open sandwiches on towel.
Cook on High 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese begins to melt.
Spread mayonnaise and/or mustard on top halves of bread.
Place tomato, lettuce and pickles on top of melted cheese.
Top off sandwiches with bread and serve.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
May be made ahead to this point.
Before serving, stir in one tray ice cubes, one bottle ginger ale and 2 pints pineapple sherbet.
Serves 12.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream together shortening, butter or margarine and sugar.
Add baking powder.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add orange drink alternately with flour. Stir in flavorings.
Turn mixture into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool until warm, then frost with frosting.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Take 4 parts genuine interest in the other person.
Strain to remove any bits of idle curiosity.
Add 1 part each of unobtrusiveness and cheerfulness and put over low heart-warming fire.

title: tuna toppers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread mixture on buttered white bread.
Cut into quarters; garnish.

title: no bake date-coconut balls
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in dates and brown sugar.

Cook, stirring constantly, until dates dissolve and mixture becomes thickened, approximately 10 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in cereal, nuts, vanilla and 1 cup coconut. Cool mixture about 10 minutes or until cool enough to shape.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: Sprinkle rice
into
x
13-inch pan.
Heat soups and water; pour
over rice.
Arrange pork chops on rice.
Sprinkle with dry onion
soup. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes without uncovering.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes and stir until Jell-O is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip; then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit, if desired. Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill 3 hours.
Garnish, if desired.

title: teriyaki tuna with fresh pineapple(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large baking dish.
Cut pineapple lengthwise into 6 spears.
Add pineapple and tuna to dish, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes, turning every 10 minutes.
Remove tuna and pineapple from marinade, reserving marinade.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray and place rack on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place tuna and pineapple on grill rack and cook 4 minutes on each side until tuna is medium-rare or desired degree of doneness, basting tuna and pineapple occasionally with reserved marinade.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings (serving size:
3 ounces fish and 1 pineapple spear).
Calories 249; fat 6.1 grams.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for ketchup.
Place in a sprayed baking dish.
Squirt ketchup on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and cook 1/2 hour longer or until done.
Set pan under dish to catch excess grease in case beef is not lean.

title: cheesy new potatoes with bacon
directions: Wash potatoes, do not peek.
Place potatoes in a small Dutch oven or pot.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and cool slightly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix potatoes, butter and seasonings.
Layer in 2 layers each in 2-quart casserole dish, potatoes, bacon and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: texas meatballs and rice(microwave)
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Place into 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High until meatballs are set and lose their pink color.
About 4 to 7 minutes.
Rearrange after 1/2 the cooking time.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover.
Microwave on High until bubbly, about 4 to 7 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato pie by reva
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° or until pie is set and the crust is brown.

title: deviled hot dogs
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in hot oil until tender.
Slice hot dogs lengthwise.
Add with remaining ingredients to onion mixture.
Simmer, uncovered.

title: tuna potato chip casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles 7 minutes.
Mix ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Simmer until thick.
Add jello and red color.
Cool.
Put layer of strawberries in bottom of baked pie shell.
Put mixture over and another layer and the rest of the mixture.
Dot with whipped cream.

title: easy fat-free frosting
directions: Beat the milk, whipped topping mix and pudding on low speed until blended and then on high speed for 4 to 6 minutes or until soft peaks form.
Makes about 3 cups.
Enough to frost a 9 x 13 cake.
Refrigerate.

title: methodist potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine 6 tablespoons butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend all with defrosted potatoes.
Pour mixture into greased large casserole.
Mix remaining butter with cornflakes and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Take flour and add baking powder; mix well.
Add enough milk to make a slightly wet dough.
Pour on floured counter.
Knead dough into egg size balls.
Roll out as flat as possible with dough roller.
Place flat into hot grease but be careful and not burn your grease.
Turn over and brown on both sides.
Cool and cover with powdered sugar or honey.

title: chicken veggie bake
directions: Mix soup and Miracle Whip.
Put in Pam sprayed pan.
Lay the chicken breasts over the top.
Add water.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Then add mixed frozen veggies or fresh broccoli spears. Continue to bake an hour or till done.
Good over potatoes or rice.
Lemon pepper or garlic pepper on chicken is good.

title: imagination dessert bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (375° for glass pan).
Combine flour, oats, and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Mix in butter.
Reserve 1 1\2 cup of mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 13x9-inch pan.
Bake 20-30 min.
Remove.
Turn oven down to 350°.
Pour condensed milk over crust.
Then use your imagination!
Use any or all of the toppings, first nuts, then coconut and then chocolate chips.
Top with reserved oat mixture.
Sprinkle over toppings and press lightly.
Bake for 30 min. or until lightly browned.

title: salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, green pepper, then celery.
Cook peas until done and drain.
Spread peas over next layer.
Spread mayonnaise on top for next layer.
Sprinkle Kraft shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; skin and tear into pieces. Place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle on dressing moistened with chicken broth (or water). Spoon on melted butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade raised rolls
directions: To cream mixture, add boiling water to sugar and Crisco.
Stir until dissolved to a liquid.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of cold water.
Add beaten egg and salt to creamed mixture.
Add yeast. Beat in sifted flour until you have a fairly soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Form rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese, and onion in bottom of pie shell. Beat together eggs, cream and seasonings and pour over mixture into shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes on bottom shelf.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking 25-35 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand for ten minutes before cutting.

title: ange's fluffy frosting
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugar and beat well.
Add milk, teaspoon at a time, then vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: shrimp curry casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Add milk all at once and continue to stir and cook over medium heat. When smooth and thickened, remove from heat and stir in noodles, shrimp and parsley.
Turn into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Remove from oven and arrange onion rings on top. Return to oven and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place over double boiler and cook. When mixture starts to boil, use an electric mixer and beat for 5 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces; roll into balls.
Roll in the 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon mixture.
Put half of balls in large Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Mix the margarine, 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon; bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Add 1/2 of mixture on top of first half of rolled biscuits.
Add the other half of rolled biscuits; top with remainder of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When slightly cooled, turn pan upside down on plate.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: In 2 quart casserole dish let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Combine softened cheese with gelatin powder.
Add hot water and mix.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and cap strawberries.
(You may slice the strawberries or leave them whole.)
In a medium saucepan combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and boil for about 1 minute.
Add lemon juice and strawberry gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Cool.
Carefully fold in strawberries.
Spread softened cream cheese on cooled crust.
Pour strawberry mixture into crust.
Let set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add butter; mix in well. Add raisins; mix well.
Beat egg and add milk in a separate bowl, then mix well with dry ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until dry in center when tested.

title: thai curry
directions: Brown chicken.
Cook vegetables separately.
Cut up chicken into chunks.
Mix rest of ingredients together and serve over rice. (Hot and spicy; adjust curry paste to taste.)

title: kathy's pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix well and pat into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat
water; dissolve jello.
Add all other ingredients and congeal.

title: cloud 9 salad
directions: Cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple juice and sugar. Cream well.
Gradually add cherries, pineapple chunks, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly, chill for 3 hours.

title: wonderful 5 minute fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Then turn heat down and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and mix with electric mixer until thick.
Pour into a buttered dish and cool.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce, eggs and other ingredients.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix together. Set aside.
Spread bean dip on a platter.
Top with half of the mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, avocados, cheese and olives. Serve with chips.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; heat cottage cheese until warm.
Put everything in bowl except flour.
Add warm cheese.
Gradually add flour until dough is stiff.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Put into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart (8-inch) round greased casserole.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
After baking, spread with butter and salt the top.

title: mil's california blend
directions: Clean and cut fresh garden vegetables.
Place vegetables in large pan with 2 cups cold water.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat back and cook until tender.
Drain.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread mix
directions: To make mix: Combine all ingredients except pumpkin in a large bowl.
Pour into a 1 quart, resealable plastic bag; seal. Place in a fabric bag.
Place bag along with can of pumpkin.

title: 3 ingredient cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9x12 inch cake pan, sprayed lightly with oil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May dust with powdered sugar after cooled.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to package directions. Cool. Meanwhile, mix jello and water. Use a large fork and poke the cake every inch or so. Pour the jello mixture over the cake and refrigerate. Mix the pudding, milk, extract and Cool Whip to make frosting and spread over cake. Keep cake refrigerated.

title: cheese cake (pie)
directions: Mix cream cheese well.
Add lemon juice, eggs and sugar.
Mix all together.
Put into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool pie 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, vanilla and 4 tablespoon sugar well.
Put on top of pie and bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients in a bowl and beat at low speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 12-cup tube pan at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool.

title: fresh peach cake and icing
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after the addition of each egg.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add gradually these 3 dry ingredients to the creamy mixture.
Add buttermilk and 2 extracts. Beat well.
Add mashed peaches.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool cakes to room temperature before icing.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies(best in the world)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar in a large mixer bowl at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture at low speed.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove cookies; cool on racks.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove bones. Use all chicken broth and add the bouillon and pepper. Knead until dough is firm, then roll out thin and cut into small pieces. Add to boiling broth; cover about 5 to 7 minutes. If you have more dumplings, let the first layer cook, then add another batch and cook same as directed. Best if not cooked too dry. Serves about 10.

title: low calorie frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain syrup from can of fruit cocktail and mix with cream cheese.
When thoroughly blended, add drained fruit, sliced banana and any other fresh fruit desired.
Place in freezer tray, stir several times during the freezing process.
Cut in slices and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries.
Chop in blender and add oranges.
Add orange peel and chop together.
Add sugar to personal taste and nuts (if desired).

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
drain.
Combine	all ingredients until thoroughly	blended.
Serve on hamburg buns and bake in hot oven, 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
May be frozen.

title: georgia powell's seven layer salad
directions: Put one layer of lettuce first and then alternate other ingredients until all are used, except mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Put the mayonnaise on the top.
Then put the Parmesan cheese on top of mayonnaise.

title: fran's salad
directions: Toss together first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix next 3 ingredients for dressing.
Add enough milk to shake and make dressing to desired thickness.

title: banana split pie
directions: Clean strawberries and rhubarb.
Slice large berries in half. Cut rhubarb into 1-inch pieces.
Late season rhubarb may need additional sugar to sweeten.
Put berries and rhubarb into a bowl and sprinkle sugar, flour, tapioca and salt over fruit.
Let stand while making pie crust.
Line pan with pie dough and put in fruit. Cover with top crust and flute edges.
A lattice top makes a pretty pie.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add melted chocolate and all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut in squares while hot.
Makes 20 brownies.

title: ham salad
directions: Ground ham in food processor. Cut up sweet pickles, eggs and onions. Mix all the ingredients together.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash turnip greens thoroughly.
Chop greens into small pieces. Put greens in pot with 4 cups water (more water may be used, if necessary).
Add sugar, salt, pepper and salt pork.
Bring to brisk boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine biscuit mix and onions in a small bowl.
Combine 2 eggs and milk; pour into biscuit mix.
Stir only until mixture is moistened.
Spoon half the batter into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Spoon on cheese mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peach-apricot delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze according to regular freezing instructions.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and ketchup together with beater until smooth. Add garlic and onion powder to your taste. Add celery and shrimp. Serve with Frito Lay large corn chips.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour, soda and
add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 layer cake.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pinch off and shape in fingers.
Bake in moderate oven on a greased cookie sheet.
When cold roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Use 1/3 cup per cup of boiling water.

title: gramma's finger jello
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate. Cut into squares when hardened.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large microwave dish. Heat on High for 3 to 5 minutes (until mixture is boiling and sugar is dissolved).
Remove and add cornflakes.
Stir thoroughly. Drop with teaspoon onto buttered pan.

title: beef stuffed acorn squash
directions: Microwave Directions:
Pierce whole squash with a fork several times. Place on paper towel. Cook on High until tender, 7 to 8 minutes, turning after 4 minutes. Set aside.

title: raisin cheese cake cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix soft butter with brown sugar. Blend in flour. Add raisins and chopped nuts.
Measure 1 cup of mixture into bottom of greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, or until golden at edges.
Cool slightly.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In a bowl combine chicken and fruit.
Arrange on lettuce-lined plate.
Mix yogurt and orange juice; drizzle over chicken mixture. Garnish with sliced cantaloupe.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients in lightly greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: white house chicken
directions: Cook broccoli spears until tender-crisp.
Drain and arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with chicken, then with mixture of undiluted soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Top with dry corn muffin mix.
Top with cheese.
Slice margarine over the top.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pear pie
directions: Sprinkle pears with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, lemon peel and flour.
Stir into pears.
Pour into crust.	Put margarine and spices
on	top
and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place grated cheese on top.	Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cream cheese and sugar, cottage cheese, cocoa, flour, Amaretto, vanilla and salt processing until smooth.
Add egg and process until blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes until cheese cake is set.
Let cool.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Garnish with chocolate curls.
Makes 200 calories per serving.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° until edges are brown, about 20 minutes.

title: my grandmother's one egg cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg.
Add flavoring.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift measured flour; sift with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed shortening.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Great for shortcake.

title: cream cheese tarts(very good!)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of 18 cupcake tins (use silver tins; I use custard cups and pot pie tins).
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put cherry or blueberry pie filling on top.

title: christmas brittle
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets and keep warm in 200° oven.
In large saucepan, combine the sugar, corn syrup and 1 cup water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a candy thermometer reaches 240° (soft ball stage).
Stir in butter, salt and peanuts.
Keep cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 300°.
Combine soda, 1 teaspoon water and vanilla.
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in soda mixture.
Quickly spread half of mixture in each pan. Spread with a spatula 1/4-inch thick.
Cool and break into pieces. Yields about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: vera's apricotties(cookies)
directions: Combine apricots, raisins, dates and juice in pan.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool.
Mix other ingredients until well blended.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Form into small balls or drop from teaspoon onto baking sheet covered with foil.
Flatten to 1/4 inch and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandma's fruit crunch
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Use nonstick electric or iron skillet.
Heat margarine in skillet, medium heat, until melted.
Add sugar.
Stir constantly until sugar mixture is all melted and turns brown and runny.
Turn off heat and quickly stir in peanuts.
Pour onto cookie sheet. Let cool, then break into pieces with back of table knife.

title: rapidrise rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water and stir good.
Mix with all other ingredients and mix until combined thoroughly.
Let rise until double.
Punch down on floured surface and knead until firm.
Pinch rolls off in balls and let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Split rolls.
Combine butter, mustard, onion and poppy seed; spread on both sides of rolls.
Place ham on bottom half; top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: country french bread slices
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine margarine and parsley.
Spread on one side of each bread slice.
Place, buttered side down, on ungreased 10 x 15 x 1-inch baking pan or cookie sheet.
Toast in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Turn bread slices buttered side up.
Cut each slice of cheese into four squares. Place two squares of cheese on top of each bread slice.
Bake for an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Take cauliflower apart and parboil for 10 minutes. Drain and put in a 9 x 9-inch casserole. Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs and pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and cool.
Add chopped boiled eggs to macaroni, Cheddar cheese, chopped green pepper, onion, pickle relish, Miracle Whip and celery salt.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
If macaroni salad is dry in the morning, add Miracle Whip.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing with 1/2 cup oleo.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: southwest hominy green chili casserole
directions: Combine hominy, chilies and butter in 1-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Microwave on Medium-low, covered, stirring once about 7 minutes.
Stir in cheese and sour cream.
Heat 2 more minutes.

title: cheese salsa
directions: In the pan you fry the chopped onions, chiles and tomatoes, take off burner and wait until it cools off a bit, then add milk and cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar and cranberries.
Let stand overnight.
Whip cream and add to mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: veggie soup
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, zucchini, etc., may be used.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar and the cream cheese until smooth, then add the remaining ingredients.
Serve in a hollowed out pumpkin.
Eat with the gingersnap cookies.
Yields 7 cups.

title: ecuadorian salsa
directions: Blend in blender the first 6 ingredients.
Chop and add to mixture the remaining ingredients.
Squeeze in lemon juice to taste.
Add 2 to 4 drops of hot pepper sauce for zest.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Sprinkle season all over chicken.
Brown on all sides in hot oil.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, breaking up tomatoes. Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: marching band brownies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over mixture.
Stir, then add the 2 eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups or 8 servings, four tablespoons per serving, 100 calories per serving.

title: kids' favorite quesadillas
directions: Heat oil in frying pan over medium-high heat.
Place tortilla in pan.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over tortilla.
Place another tortilla over cheese creating a "sandwich." Flip when cheese begins to melt.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Cut with pizza cutter into wedges.
Serve wedges with salsa, sour cream or cottage cheese for dipping!
Kids love it.

title: beefy-vegetable spears
directions: Combine cream cheese and horseradish.
Spread 1 tablespoon of the mixture on doubled beef slices.
Place 1 vegetable spear in center and roll.
Chill until served.

title: velvet corn soup
directions: In a medium bowl stir together chicken, corn, 1 egg white and salt.
In large saucepan heat chicken broth to boiling.
Stir in chicken mixture.
Stir together cornstarch and water until smooth. Add to chicken broth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, and boil 1 minute.
Slowly stir in slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with ham.
Serve immediately.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in a greased shallow baking dish; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, remove chicken from baking dish.
Serve gravy over rice and place chicken breast on mound of rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: banana caramel pie
directions: Boil Eagle Brand milk (unopened) in water for 3 hours.
Make sure water level is over can at all times during boiling.
After 3 hours, let can cool.
Put in refrigerator until cold.
Open and spread in graham cracker crust.
Cut bananas in small slices and place over Eagle Brand.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: black bean tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add green and red peppers to saute until tender.
Add salsa, cumin, black beans and stewed tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Coat 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray.
Put 1 1/2 cups bean mixture on bottom. Cover beans with 1/2 of tortillas.
Sprinkle on 1/3 of cheese.
Spread 2 1/2 cups of bean mixture over cheese.
Layer on remaining tortillas, 1/3 cheese and remaining bean mixture.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: scrapple
directions: Blend corn meal and 1 cup water in a small bowl.
In a large saucepan, combine sausage, sage, salt, parsley and chicken broth. Gradually stir in 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn meal slowly to boiling mixture.
Stir constantly with a wire whisk. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Turn into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Dot top with a little butter.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: quick and easy shortbread
directions: Mix all together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: simple sweet scones
directions: Heat
oven
Put flour, baking powder and salt into a
large bowl;
stir to mix well.
Add butter and cut in with pastry
blender
or
rub
in with your fingers until the mixture looks
like
fine granules.
Add sugar;
toss to mix. Add
milk and
stir with a fork until soft dough forms.
Form dough into
a ball; put on a lightly floured board and give 10 to 12 kneads. Roll out dough to about 12 x 5 1/2-inches.	Cut with
a
2-inch cutter.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Delicious with
butter
and honey
or preserves.
Makes eighteen 2-inch rounds.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until well done; cool and debone.
Reserve broth. Place 1 pie crust in shallow baking dish.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces (square or round is best) and place on top of crust. Sprinkle chopped egg over meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with 1 cup sugar and set aside.
In a deep 9 x 9 pan, melt margarine. In a mixing bowl, mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Pour the fruit mixture over the flour mixture.
Do not stir.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Add maraschino cherries.
Cut in half; do not add juice.
Mix well; chill.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serve as salad or dessert.

title: pierogi made easy
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Boil potatoes until tender when tested with fork.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Saute butter and onions in a small skillet.
When the potatoes are done, mash them and add the cheese and mash together.
In your baking dish, place 3 lasagna noodles.
On top of the noodles, spread out 1/3 of the potato/cheese mixture over that.
Follow with layers as listed. Put the last three lasagna noodles on top and rest of the onions and butter.
Cover and bake in 225° oven for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon pasta salad
directions: Cut bell peppers into strips and saute in lightly oiled skillet.
Remove and add almonds, stirring over high heat 30 seconds.
Remove peel from lemon using grater and set aside.
Cut off white pith; discard.
Cut lemon into 1/4-inch slices.
Into hot oiled skillet, add leeks, lemon peel, lemon slices, capers, salt and pepper.
Stir and toss until vegetables are tender-crisp. Remove from heat and discard lemon slices.
Stir in almond and bell pepper slices.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cook pasta; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine with veggies.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Add sugar and shortening, beat well.
Add egg and stir in molasses and buttermilk.
Sift together all dry ingredients several times.
Add to cake mixture.
Add additional flour to make dough stiff.
Knead on floured board.
Divide into 5 portions. Bake each in 9-inch cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake about 10 minutes at 370°.
Stack layers with dried fruit in between each layer.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer as listed in a covered casserole dish.
Top layer should be the raw bacon strips.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry squash(microwave)
directions: Cut 1-inch off tops of squash.
Remove seeds.
Combine cranberries, brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Pack half of mixture into each squash.
Dot with butter.
Add squash to 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover loosely with heavy-duty plastic wrap.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and add onion.
Simmer.
Add bacon and beans.
Add catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexicali chicken pasta salad
directions: Prepare salad as directed on package except omit oil from dressing and mix in sour cream and red pepper.
Stir in chicken. Line serving plate with tortilla chips.
Mound salad onto chips. Top with tomato and cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and crisco together.
Add sugar - one cup at a time.
Cream well.
Add eggs - one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk slowly. Begin with flour and end with flour using low speed - Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Pour jello straight from package into cottage cheese; mix well.
Add orange slices and Cool Whip.
Let set overnight.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pot, brown beef and drain.
Add onion, then remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Cook over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot with grated cheese and chips.
Freezes well.

title: cocoa mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mrs. goenner's caramels
directions: Mix all together, except for pecans, stirring all the time. Cook to 240°.
Add chopped nuts, if desired. (Must have low humidity.
It takes 30 minutes to cook.)
Pour into well-greased cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dry wieners between paper towels.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and corn meal. Add oil, egg and milk.
Stir until mixed.
Dip wieners into mixture to coat and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
This batter can also be used to make onion rings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Will be brown.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine and spread into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: creamed cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in a saucepan; add 1 inch of water and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 6-7 minutes, or until crisp-tender; drain. Grease the bottom and sides of a 2 quart baking dish; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons bread crumbs. Add cauliflower. Pour cream over top. Dot with butter; sprinkle with remaining salt and bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until cauliflower is tender. Garnish with parsley.

title: lisa's hot chili
directions: Brown beef in large saucepan with onion; and 1 T. olive oil and 3 chopped garlic cloves.
Add all ingredients but beans and cook uncovered on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans then heat to boiling point and serve.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar gradually until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Freeze in a 1-gallon churn type freezer.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all together.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken cutlets with peppers and mushrooms
directions: Fill pan with olive oil just to cover bottom.
Heat on low. Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Fry with garlic cloves (cut up). When the chicken turns white, add peppers, mushrooms, salt and pepper to your taste; simmer for 1/2 hour on low heat.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar and mix.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and soda. Add oil.
Bake in greased muffin tins or paper liners in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oleo in double boiler till transparent.
Mix in remaining ingredients and heat till cheese melts.
Serve hot. If too thick, add a little milk.

title: easy squirrel or chicken dumplings
directions: Put squirrel in iron pot with onion, garlic, bell pepper, Season-All, salt and oil.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until tender.
Remove everything from iron pot and put in big pot.
Bring to a rolling boil; add mushroom soup and let dissolve into boiling water.

Keep it at a rolling boil; then take biscuits out of can and pinch small piece off and drop into pot. When all of the biscuits are added, stir a little, reduce heat, turn off when the swelling in the biscuits go down, approximately 15 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: easy snackin
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Spread on 2 slices of bread and eat with a tall glass of cold milk.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Saute onions and peppers in oleo until soft.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine noodles, salmon, soup, peppers and onions.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: grandma's pineapple surprise
directions: *If using pineapple in juice, increase sugar to 1 cup.

title: low-fat easy dinner for 4
directions: Heat soup over medium heat or in microwave.
Add kielbasa and peas; simmer.
Cook eggs and noodles as directed.
Drain.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Stir.
Serve with side salad (fat-free dressing).

title: pie shell crust
directions: Mix with fork the flour and shortening until well blended. Add 1 tablespoon at a time (approximately 5 tablespoons) until ingredients hold together.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and cornflakes.
Blend mixture well.
Spoon yogurt mixture over chicken to coat well. Cover chicken and refrigerate overnight.
Coat each chicken breast with cornflakes.
Place chicken in shallow nonstick dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown; baste once.

title: mixed bean soup
directions: Rinse beans, then cover with cold water overnight.
Drain beans and return to the pot.
Add 6 cups of broth, tomatoes and spices.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper, carrots and garlic to soup.
Simmer uncovered over medium heat 20 minutes.
Add more stock or broth if necessary to keep beans covered.
Stir in parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: meatballs
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix in ground beef, pepper and salt until evenly mixed.
Make 2-inch meatballs.
Lightly brown in skillet, then place meatballs in sauce or gravy and cook for about 20 minutes.
Meatballs will be tender and juicy.
Yields 20 to 25 meatballs.

title: barbecue venison(terrific for tough pieces of venison)
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Pour water and vinegar over and add spices.
Bring to boil, then simmer on low heat for at least 6 hours.
This is a super recipe for the crock-pot.
Put it on before you go to bed and let it cook overnight.
You may be tempted to eat it at this stage, if you do just add 6 to 8 gingersnap cookies (crumbled) to the sauce and pour over sliced meat.

title: almond buttercrunch candy
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8-inch or 9-inch cake pan with aluminum foil.
Butter foil heavily and set aside.
Combine all ingredients in a 10-inch skillet and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Working quickly, spread candy into prepared pan. Cool about 15 minutes or until firm.
Remove candy by lifting edges of foil.
Cool thoroughly.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, chilies, picante sauce, onion and garlic powder by hand or mixer until well blended.
Spread on tortillas; roll up. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours or up to 3 days. Cut each roll into desired size slices.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 50 appetizers.

title: lemon lush
directions: 1st Step (Crust):
Combine butter, sugar, flour and pecans. Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: wontons for soup or frying
directions: Mix together all ingredients except wonton skins and egg. Take each wonton skin, coat all 4 edges with egg.
In center put about teaspoon filling.
Fold over in triangle, sealing all edges, take both ends, dabbing one end with egg and fold together forming a "crown" or wonton.
Make sure meat filling is firmly sealed within.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix paprika and garlic and sprinkle steak strips.
Let set a few minutes.
Brown meat in butter, when well-browned; add beef broth and simmer 45 minutes. Add vegetables to broth and meat and simmer for 7 minutes.
Mix cornstarch water and soy sauce and work into
a paste.
Add to meat and vegetables and cook until thickened.
Serve over wild rice or chow mein noodles.

title: great milk shake
directions: Process all in blender for 30 seconds or until frothy.

title: copper pennies
directions: Make a sauce of last 8 ingredients and pour over first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Tastes good cold.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Heap pie plate with sliced apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; pour over apples.
Mix butter, brown sugar and flour. Crumble this mixture over top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs(low calorie)
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash yolks.
Add cottage cheese, skim milk and horseradish; mix well.
Then return to halved egg whites.
Top with sprinkle of paprika or dry minced parsley.
Makes 12 servings.
One serving equals 48 calories or 1 lean meat exchange.

title: cheese danish
directions: Blend sugar, egg yolk and lemon juice until smooth.
Add cheese and vanilla. Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pinch seams together.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over rolls.
Top with remaining package of crescent rolls. Mix egg white with 1 teaspoon water.
Brush on top of rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast almonds 5 minutes.
Cool.
Grease muffin tins or use foil or paper baking cups.
Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Break eggs into another bowl; add pumpkin and butter and whisk until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour over dry ingredients and fold in with a rubber spatula just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Scoop batter into cups and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until springy to touch.
Turn out on rack to cool.
Wrap in plastic bag and keep for 1 to 2 days.
Reheat before serving.
Makes 12 regular or 24 miniature muffins.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Slice cake layers in half.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Prepare pudding as directed.
In large glass bowl layer ingredients:
Jell-O, cake and pudding.
End with cake on top.
Spread with Cool Whip on top.

title: jay's special
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and bell peppers together.
Drain off excess fat.
Add hot water, Heinz 57 sauce, tomatoes, macaroni, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium to low heat until water has cooked out.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in rice and marshmallows. Add pineapple juice and chill until mixture begins to thicken. Stir in pineapple and chopped apple to which lemon juice has been added.
Chill until nearly set, and fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: amish barbecue sauce
directions: Melt in saucepan.
Brush on meat frequently throughout grilling.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar twin, egg, applesauce and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook meat in skillet and drain.
Dissolve bouillon cube in the
water.
Mix shredded cabbage, sliced carrots, chopped onion, garlic,
bouillon broth, pepper and salt with the meat; toss well. Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: orange mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cream cheese and mix well.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Spray vegetable spray on mold and pour into mold.
Chill 2 hours.

title: hello dollies
directions: In a 7 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish, make crust with graham cracker crumbs and butter.
On top of this, sprinkle nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients and seasonings; add to pumpkin mixture.
Fold in well.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn out on towel sprinkled heavily with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together. Let cool.

title: michele's turkey joes
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until onion is translucent. Crumble in ground turkey; saute 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and red pepper.
Stir to mix.
Stir in barbecue and chili sauces.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: football chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add beans and soup.
Cook 10 minutes. Make a paste of chili powder, flour, water and salt.
Add to meat mixture and heat over low heat for approximately 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: orange spread
directions: Mix well.
Spread on crackers, bread or spice cake.

title: baked buttercup squash
directions: Wash and cut squash in half.
Scoop out seeds and strings. Bake outside down in a dish with a little water at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Scoop from shell and mash with butter. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples in cider until tender and thick, approximately 1 hour.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch space in top.
Adjust lids.
Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Yield:
5 pints.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, chopped onion, salt, pepper, cream of chicken soup, shredded Cheddar cheese and sour cream together.
Melt 2 sticks butter.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix crackers and butter together.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter. Add marshmallows. Cook at low heat and stir constantly until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and stir well. Press firmly into cake pan. When warm, cut.
Cool.

title: rum-m-m balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in little balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: original chili soup
directions: While meat is browning, add onion and pepper.
When tender, add sauce, juice and beans.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: russian shrimp salad
directions: Cut everything into small pieces.
Mix together and add mayonnaise, salt, horseradish and lemon juice to taste.
One is free to add to this salad apple, avocado, green pepper, etc.

title: veal cutlets cordon bleu(serves 6)
directions: Pound the veal with meat cleaver until very thin.
Season with the salt and pepper to taste.
Put cheese and ham slice on top of each of 6 slices of veal and top with remaining veal.
Pound edges together.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Melt chips in a small amount of butter.
Spread over mixture. Chill and cut into squares.

title: italian bread dip
directions: Cut up green pepper, ham and green onion tops.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Good Seasons dressing.
Mix both mixtures together.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: To make the dough, mix water with flour.
Next, roll out the dough and then cut into small strips about an inch in width.
Then sprinkle lots of cinnamon and sugar on the strips.
Roll the strips.
Put the cinnamon rolls into the oven for about 30 minutes.
Then they're ready to eat!

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and garlic powder in medium bowl.
Stir in milk, egg and onion until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into deep hot oil (375°); fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Save 1/2 of this and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla for 4 or 5 minutes.
Fold in strawberries.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs. Cover with foil.
Freeze.
Serves 12.
Remove for 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir the sugar, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all dry ingredients).
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave on High power for 2 minutes or until butter melts.
Add peanut butter and stir vigorously until mixture is smooth.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan or large cookie sheet.
Pat crescent roll dough into pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until brown.
Mix together cream cheese, dry dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread on cooled, baked crust.
Grate vegetables; sprinkle and layer with cheese over the cream cheese mixture and chill.
Just before serving, slice into bite-size pieces and arrange on serving dish.

title: dawn's mexican casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with one layer of tortillas.
Mix beef, soup and tomatoes together.
Pour over tortillas.
Put another layer of tortillas on top.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Place
chicken
in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top each piece with Swiss cheese.
Place mushrooms over the cheese.
Mix the soup with the wine and pour over chicken. Spread stuffing mix over top and drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: graham cracker fudge
directions: Mix crumbs and flour; set aside.
Put oleo, milk and sugar in pan; bring to boil.
Add chocolate bits, stirring until melted. Add crumb mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into lightly buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ham-n-potato church soup
directions: Brown butter; add onions and cook a little.
Add a gallon of milk.
Mix 6 to 7 cups flour with some milk and add to boiling milk.
When thickened, add cheese, salt, pepper and chicken base to suit taste.
Now add the rest of the hot milk, ham and potatoes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all together; drop by spoonfuls into skillet.
Fry in mixed butter and lard until brown and crisp.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix and make into small balls; put in crock-pot on high 2 to 3 hours with:

title: old-fashioned apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Beat sugar, eggs and oil together.
Mix flour and cinnamon; add to sugar mixture.
Stir well; then add apples.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza(everyone loves this!)
directions: Spread a 9 x 13-inch baking sheet with crescent roll dough. Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Mix dressing mix, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled dough.
Add vegetables and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: spanakopeta (spinach pie)
directions: Saute onion in oil and butter (5 to 6 tablespoons).
Lightly blend room temperature cheeses.
Add eggs and blend.
Add cooked and strained spinach to onion mixture.
Add dill, salt and pepper. Cook about 10 minutes until just dry.
Add spinach mixture to cheeses.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons butter to mixture.
Brush bottom of 10 x 15-inch casserole dish with butter; add 1 sheet of filo, brush with butter.
Add next sheet; brush with butter, etc., rounding each up the side of pan until you have used half of the filo sheets.
Add spinach mixture to pan; add remaining filo, sheet by sheet, tucking in edges to seal.
Score top into 2 or 3-inch squares.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: vegetable soup mixtures
directions: Mix all vegetables and boil 5 minutes or pack raw.
Pack loosely into clean jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart jar.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight. Yields 7 to 8 pints.
Process:
pints 40 minutes, quarts 40 minutes, 10 pounds pressure.
Any combination of vegetables may be used.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like pie dough.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
While crust is baking, mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over crust while still warm.
Mix milk and lemon pudding together. Spread over top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Serve in squares.

title: corn fritters
directions: Separate eggs.
Sift flour.
Combine all ingredients, except the egg whites.
Stir mixture until smooth.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks; fold this into mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil (Wesson, sunflower, etc.).
Cook until golden brown; turn for even graining on both sides.
Drain on paper towel. Serve hot with or without syrup of your choice.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together sugar sugar and eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour and baking soda.
Slowly add flour to egg mixture, mixing thoroughly. Blend in vanilla; fold in pineapple and nuts.
Pour batter into an ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. (Caution--do not overbake.)
Spread icing over hot cake and serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. Combine all ingredients; slow cook in crock-pot.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, chunk and boil potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes and add other ingredients as desired.

title: banana nut bread(in blender)
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Add chopped walnuts.
Put into blender the sugar, butter, egg, bananas and milk; cover.
Press button 8 to 15 seconds or until all is blended.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on, peel and mash.
Combine all the ingredients and place in casserole.

title: bark
directions: Place the soda crackers side by side on a large cookie sheet that has been lined with a buttered piece of foil.
Heat and boil the sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Pour over the crackers.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 400° oven.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle the chocolate bits on top.
When they start to melt, spread the chocolate evenly over the top.
When the Bark is cool, break into nice sized eating pieces.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Marinate above in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.
Grill approximately 10 minutes each side.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, vanilla, soda and water or milk. Add eggs; mix all well. Add flour until you have a soft dough. Use as much flour as needed. Roll out into balls (golf ball size). Flatten 2 to 3-inch size. Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° or 375° for 15 minutes. Best baked on cookie sheets lined with foil or wax paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool.
When cool, add whipped cream.
Mix well together; fold into a mixture of remaining ingredients.
Mix altogether.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Prepare muffin pans, grease sides and bottoms.
Mix dry ingredients together in medium bowl.
Mix other ingredients together and add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: manning cookies
directions: Beat together butter and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Blend together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture, blending well.
Add chopped nuts.
Roll dough into two balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 1 hour in the refrigerator.
Flatten dough out and cut into 15 to 16 equal size pieces.
Shape into small, marble-sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes each sheet until firm but not brown.
While warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Boil all except Jell-O
until sugar is dissolved. Take off heat; wait 7 minutes, then add Jell-O.
Mix until dissolved.
Put hot in jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Boil chicken for about 30 to 45 minutes; drain and cool.
Tear chicken into thin pieces.
Add cream cheese.
Sprinkle salt over entire chicken.
Add about 1 tablespoon pepper.
Add almonds.
Cut up onion and add.
Stir in milk.
Melt butter in microwave.
Open crescent rolls and add mixture, everything except butter, onto crescent rolls, usually a teaspoon.
Close rolls and put on baking pan.
Pour melted butter over rolls and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper; drain well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix rest of ingredients; add to sausage mixture. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until not real juicy.

title: french toast
directions: Remove ends from loaf of bread.
Cut crosswise in 1-inch thick slices.
Arrange bread slices in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple cinnamon pancakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Sift all dry ingredients together in a separate bowl. Add milk
mixture to flour mixture. Stir just until flour is dampened. Adjust milk as necessary to achieve heavy cream consistency. Cook in a nonstick skillet.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together soft oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift and add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Chill and roll balls walnut size.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
In bowl, mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, milk and salt.
Pour over butter.
To fruit, add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple souffle or dutch pancake
directions: In blender or mixer, combine first 7 ingredients.
Melt margarine in a 12 x 13-inch dish in oven.
Place sliced apples and brown sugar on bottom of dish in melted margarine.
Return to oven.
When sizzling, pour batter over apples, brown sugar and margarine.
Bake 20 minutes in preheated 425° oven or until puffed and brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, water, eggs and oil.
Add sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and flour.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain, set aside.
Combine next 3 ingredients in a medium skillet.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until cranberry sauce melts.
Add carrots and stir gently.
Heat thoroughly stirring constantly.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: jello mold
directions: Blend Jell-O and hot water.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Fold in pineapple and juice.
Blend in baby apricots and mayonnaise. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: peach pan dessert
directions: Melt margarine. Mix margarine, sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and lemon juice. Add the peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Bake in 400° to 450° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and slice into 1/4-inch strips. In a bowl, layer sweet potatoes, crushed graham crackers (to cover potatoes), brown sugar and pineapple chunks (to cover potatoes).
Repeat layers once more.
Pour juice from can of pineapple over the top of the layers.

title: coconut-butterscotch dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: spinach stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions until tender. Squeeze out all water.
Set aside.
Twist out stems of mushrooms and chop fine and saute in small amount of butter.
Add small amount of minced onion and saute; add bread crumbs and cheese. Stir mixture.
Dip mushroom caps in melted butter.
Stuff caps with mixture; will be rounded on top of mushroom.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ten minute szechuan chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Toss lightly with cornstarch in paper bag.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet; add chicken and garlic.
Stir-fry until chicken is lightly browned.
Add soy sauce, vinegar and water.
Cover.
Cook 3 minutes.
Uncover; add onions (and cayenne pepper, if desired).
Heat 2 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: chewy nut bar
directions: Mix together and spread over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat ball sauce
directions: Make meatballs and brown lightly in olive oil, then put them in the above sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and slice thin.
Brown bacon; crumble and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon fat.
Make a sauce with the remaining ingredients and add to onions.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add bacon and potatoes, mixing well.
Cool and refrigerate, overnight if possible.
Heat before serving. This salad improves with age.

title: english apple pie(no crust to roll - 9-inch pie plate)
directions: Mix
together
until
fluffy
the
butter or margarine, brown sugar,
flour,
teaspoon of cinnamon, cold water and pecans
or walnuts.
Peel
and slice the apples into pie pan. Mix
together granulated
sugar
and
1 teaspoon of cinnamon. Pour over apples. Spoon nut topping over apples.
Batter will be thick.
Just dollop on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shoney strawberry pie
directions: Line your pie shell or crust with strawberries.
Mix water, sugar, syrup and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture is clear.
Turn off heat and add strawberry Jell-O, a few drops of red food color and a dash of salt.
Blend well.
Pour over strawberries and chill thoroughly. Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash and onion. Drain. Add remaining ingredients except crushed crackers.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: hot cherry tea
directions: Brew tea using tea bags and 6 cups water, set aside.
Heat 1 quart water, cinnamon, cloves, and sugar in a pot simmering for 30 minutes.
Add gelatin to hot mixture,
stirring to dissolve, cool, then strain and add to tea along with remaining ingredients, blending well.
Serve hot.

title: feta cheese pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drizzle olive oil over pasta and add crumbled Feta cheese.

title: chocolate-pistachio ice cream pie
directions: Spoon coffee ice cream in shell; spread evenly.
Top with scoops of selected ice cream.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze at least 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix in order and add to crust.
Refrigerate.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar.
Press on bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
