In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely and top with whipped topping.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add Jell-O pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 of the cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into the cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Decorate with gummy worms and frogs, candy flowers or chopped nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil; set aside to cool. Makes a bottle.

title: fresh peach custard pie
directions: Fill homemade or prepared pie crust with fresh peach or nectarine slices.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water and 1 tablespoon of sugar on top.
Put in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Then, beat together eggs, butter, sugar and flour.
Pour over peaches and cook at 350° until set, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain artichokes; put small amount of marinade in frypan.
Add onion and garlic to frypan; saute until limp.
Chop artichokes. Add all ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with Parmesan, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour, until set. Cool; cut into squares.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Mix together 1 cup butter, sugar, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla, 1 teaspoon salt, oatmeal and flour in mixing bowl.
Spread 3/4 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a double boiler, mix together chocolate chips, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 2 tablespoons butter and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Stir until chocolate chips are melted.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cook blueberries on the stove with lemon rind and 1/2 cup sugar until all sugar dissolves.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 8x8-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Mix together milk, flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour flour mixture into baking dish with melted butter.
Add blueberries and bake until crust has risen and turned golden brown.

title: easy make fruit cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together to make a batter and pour over melted butter.
Pour sweetened fruit over batter and bake in a 450° oven for about 1/2 hour until thick and bubbly.

title: libby's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix milk, cocoa and sugar together.
Bring to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Add butter, oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Pour in broth and boil 1 minute.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, spray Pam.
Add potatoes and onion.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes.
Pour broth mixture over chops.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover the last few minutes.

title: spicy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil.
Put a layer of onion in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Arrange chops over onions.
Cover with remaining onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops. Bake, covered, 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve on plain or parsley buttered rice.

title: quahog cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Drop into hot grease by mixing spoonful. Fry, turning once.
Serve with butter.
My wife and I eat this many.

title: apple pie with crumb topping
directions: Using pastry blender, cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add boiling water until all flour is blended.
To roll dough, use Saran Wrap on bottom and top, roll out, remove top layer of Saran Wrap. Flip dough onto pie pan.
Remove other Saran Wrap.
Very flaky with easy clean-up.
Makes 9 inch crust.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in large Dutch oven until tender; add next nine ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with potato masher.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Yields 10 cups.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
In small bowl, stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stumpf
directions: Put meat, potatoes, onion and salt into a large cooking pot. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat and potatoes are tender (2 to 4 hours).
Add water as needed. Add spices halfway through cooking.
Continue to simmer until mixture reaches desired consistency.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Taste to see if more juice is needed.

title: white cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder, one cup and one teaspoon at a time.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes (cake) or 20 minutes (cupcakes).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix well into stuffing mix. Spray baking dish with Pam. Layer half of stuffing mix in dish. Add chicken. Combine soups and sour cream. Mix well and pour over chicken. Put the rest of the stuffing on top. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: smoothie
directions: You need a little kid to help press the buttons and count to 10.
Bigger kids can do the whole thing.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain off fat.
Separate crescent rolls; place in ungreased pizza pan (or a large baking pan, 9 x 15-inch) with points towards center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: wanieta's potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion and cheese. Combine soups with sour cream; pour over top.
Cut margarine into little pieces and put on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli with easy hollandaise
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until just heated through.
Serve over drained broccoli.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Easy to fix and good.
Just as good reheated.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package. Combine cooked macaroni, butter, cheese and salt.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend together the eggs and milk and pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger paprika
directions: Brown beef; pour off excess drippings.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add water and stir in gravy mix and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and 1 cup of the onions.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Serve with noodles.
Use remaining onions over each serving.

title: quick bread
directions: Mix well and let rise 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Work down; make into ball and let rise another hour or longer.
Bake 375 degrees until done.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Cook celery and onions in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add flour, then stir in soup.
Cook and stir mixture until thick and bubbly.
Stir in noodles.
Turn noodle mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle top of casserole with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix ingredients and roll out.
Spread peanut butter.
Roll up and refrigerate.
Cut into pieces when cool.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Trim and break up cauliflower.
Cover with water and boil, simmer 2 minutes and drain.
Put in pot with broth, rice, salt and pepper and simmer 30 minutes.
Put in blender and puree.
Put in pot with milk, nutmeg and cayenne; simmer.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Cook on top of the stove until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: yam souffle
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, whip and pour into a greased dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix flour and sugar, add coconut and pecans, then add butter a little at a time.
Take potatoes out of oven and crumble on topping, put back in oven until top is brown.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well and add water, cinnamon and apples (cut apples in half and core, unpeeled).
Cover and cook until apples are soft.
Spoon sauce over apples occasionally, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese strata(serves 10)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole with margarine.
Trim bread and place in dish.
Cover with cheese.
Cover with 2nd layer of bread. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese in dish, letting soak.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until puffy.
Serves 10.
(A good brunch dish.)

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180°C).
Scrub potatoes and slice thinly with skins left on.
Place in casserole.
Add salt and pepper. Toss lightly with fork.
Place oil in frying pan and brown pork chops over medium heat.
Remove chops from pan and place on top of potatoes.

title: super chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; debone and skin and put in casserole.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup and pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers over this, about 1/2 inch thick.
Melt oleo and pour over chicken mixture.
You can sprinkle poppy seed over this.
Bake about 30 minutes, until brown at 350°.

title: toffee crumbles
directions: Lay graham crackers on large jelly roll pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (watch closely). Immediately sprinkle on nuts.
Cool and cut.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Combine all ingredients, but pretzels; pour over pretzels. Stir to coat.
Place in oven at 250° for about 20 minutes.

title: will's favorite white pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together with mixer and spoon into pie crust.
Cool before serving.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat
egg yolks
slightly.
Set
whites
aside.
Add milk. Stir in sugar,
flour,
nutmeg
and
rhubarb.
Top with butter. Cook 50 to 60 minutes in an unbaked single pie shell. Top pie with meringue.
Beat
whites of eggs until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and a pinch
of salt.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: refrigerator pickles(with vinegar)
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in a gallon container.
Combine salt, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric. Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Place container in refrigerator. Stir each day for a week.
Package in freezer boxes or bags. Freeze or refrigerate for 3 weeks.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Put the white sugar and Karo on stove; heat just enough to melt sugar.
Whip in the peanut butter.
Add the flavoring. Crush the corn flakes; stir into mixture.
Drop from spoon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May be cooked in chicken broth.

title: coconut crisps
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture, vanilla and oats, then coconut.
Like all crisp oatmeal cookies, these spread, so leave plenty of room on baking sheets.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar until smooth and pour over base.
Then sprinkle one cup chopped pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs into sugar.
Add potatoes and mix together.
Stir milk into potatoes; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding, pineapple and juice, marshmallows and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Decorate with walnuts if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Blend in butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Gently pour syrup mixture over nuts. Bake at 300° about 50 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn out on floured board.
Roll as thin as possible and cut in strips.
Drop in boiling chicken or turkey broth and cook until done.

title: crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons butter.
Saute onions, then add bell peppers, garlic and green onions; saute for 5 minutes.
Add crawfish or shrimp.
Let cook for about 20 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel, cream of mushroom soup, golden mushroom soup and cream of celery soup; let simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on rice.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and heat pie shell.
Spread half of cherry pie filling in bottom of shell.
Bake 15 minutes or just until crust is golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a small bowl, with mixer, beat cheese with sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over hot cherry pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes; cool completely and add other half of filling.

title: brownie fudge cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour and set aside in a bowl.
In a saucepan, put the oleo, oil, cocoa and water. Bring to a rapid boil and pour over dry ingredients. Add soda, vanilla, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked caramel popped corn
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan melt butter, stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, boil again over medium heat without stirring for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in baking soda and vanilla.
In a large bowl have ready the popped corn.
Pour hot syrup over it.
Turn coated popcorn onto a buttered cookie sheet or roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove and cool in pan completely.
Loosen with a spatula and break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts caramel corn.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place cut up chicken in a baking dish. Cook chicken for 30 minutes. Mix 57 sauce, honey and pineapple juice in a bowl. Pour the mixture over chicken and bake for 25 minutes longer. Make sure chicken is done and no longer pink. Add pineapple slices to top of chicken and bake 5 minutes.

title: wild rice pilaf
directions: In nonstick saucepan, heat 1/2 cup broth.
When boiling, add onion and garlic and cook until softened.
Add lemon rind and rice; stir well to coat vegetables.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups broth.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer, slowly, for 65 to 75 minutes, until rice is tender.
Stir in sesame seed. Place in bowl and garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: sausage chowder
directions: In 2-cup saucepan over medium heat, cook sausage until browned stirring to separate sausage into bite sized pieces; spoon off fat. Add water stirring to loosen brown bits.
Stir in soup until well blended.
Add milk, celery, onions, parsley and carrots; heat to simmering.
Do not boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover, simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 5 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli 15 minutes. Add pinch of salt while cooking. Drain and save water. Saut onion in butter until transparent. Add garlic and stir well. Add mushrooms, soup and Tabasco sauce. Combine all ingredients and cook over slow fire until well blended. If too thick, add reserved broccoli water. Serve in chafing dish.

title: spicy cider
directions: You will need measuring cups, 2 quart saucepan, wooden spoon and cups or mugs.
Adult supervision is needed.

title: pineapple-banana jello salad
directions: Mix Jello according to box.
Cool (not thick).
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Add pineapple to Jello.
Cover with marshmallows. Slice bananas, drop on top of marshmallows.
Let mixture gel.
Mix together:
sugar, flour, butter, beaten egg, and pineapple juice. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat, add cream cheese.
Beat with beaters.
Let cool.
Beat 2 envelopes Dream Whip and add to above. Spread this mixture over Jello.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: combination punch
directions: Mix the juices and
let
stand
an hour or two to blend the flavors.
Pour in ginger ale and serve over ice.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: To juice and grated rind of one orange, add butter and boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Add with one beaten egg to dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and cranberries, chopped.
Mix well.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Store in refrigerator (wrap in foil).

title: quick stickie buns
directions: In large bowl, mix flour plus dry yeast. Heat water, milk, butter, sugar and salt until warm. Pour into yeast mixture, add egg and beat on high speed of mixer for three (3) minutes. By hand stir in 1 3/4 cups flour. Cover and let rise for 30 minutes. While dough is rising combine topping ingredients.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple until jello dissolves.
When mixture cools, add cheese and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Place in mold or bowl and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add topping.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor; blend until all veggies are chopped.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 1 cup.

title: daffodil delight
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan according to box directions.
Cool. Cream the cream cheese at room temperature with 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
In different bowl, mix vanilla pudding, but use 1 1/2 cups milk.
Then mix cream cheese and pudding together and spoon over cooled cake.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread on top of pudding and cream cheese mix.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple. Sprinkle crushed nuts on top and refrigerate.

title: placzak (coffee cake)
directions: To warm milk, add yeast, 1 cup flour and 4 tablespoons sugar. Put in warm place with no draft to raise.
Put together remaining milk and butter.
Heat until butter is melted.
Pour milk and butter mixture in a large bowl.
Add eggs, remaining sugar, flour, nutmeg, raisins and vanilla.
Mix together well.
Add yeast mixture and gently fold in.
Cover and let raise 1 1/2 hours. Divide batter into 3 well-greased medium bread pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut in small pieces.
Mix first 3 ingredients and place in 2 quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle on top of mixture in dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water and cool.
Mix Jell-O, pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into pan and gel.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Grease baking pan with olive oil.
Put rice into pan.
Mix 16 ounces of water and 2 ounces of olive oil.
Pour into rice.
Mix in peas and pimientos.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Serves 4.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk in top of double boiler or microwave.
Combine cake mix with remaining milk and melted butter. Spread 1/2 of cake mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Spread chips and nuts on cake and cover with melted caramels.
Pour remaining cake mixture over caramels and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brownies are firm to touch.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix sifted flour, salt	and
baking
powder.
Hand mix. Do not use electric mixer.
Then
add
eggs,
oil, lemon rind, sugar and milk to flour
mixture
with
a whisk.
Fill floured and
greased pans 1/2 full.
Baker's
Joy
spray
works	best. Makes 3 loaf pans (regular) or 6 small pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken and sausage with rigatoni
directions: Remove skin; cut each breast into 4 pieces.
In a large, heavy skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Brown chicken; remove.
Add whole sausage; cook for at least 20 minutes.
Brown on all sides. Remove and cut sausage in 1-inch lengths.
Add more olive oil to skillet.
Add onion, carrot, garlic and green pepper.
Cook down until light golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients, then chicken pieces and sausage.
Cover; reduce heat to moderate-low and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover; cook for another 20 minutes to thicken sauce.
Serve over rigatoni, spaghetti or twisted egg noodles. Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli about 2 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix.

title: lo-cal chicken
directions: Salt chicken with Nature's Seasons and chill overnight.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Spoon over chicken and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 40 minutes more or until chicken is tender.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Place egg, sugar, water and baking powder over boiling water in top of double boiler.
Beat as it cooks with rotary egg beater. When it clings as a mass in the egg beater, remove from heat. Continue beating a few seconds.
Add flavoring.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Delicious with raw vegetables such as celery, carrots, kohlrabi, cauliflower, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package and drain well. Put in 2-quart dish and add well-drained tuna or you may use cooked chopped chicken, turkey or ham.
Pour mushroom soup diluted with milk.
Sprinkle this with Cheddar cheese or cheese of choice. Top this off with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 5.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in small portion of salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Mix together the soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash mixture.
Mix together stuffing and melted butter.
Spread half on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, then all the squash mixture.
Then top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Fry in deep fryer or skillet until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Eat warm.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef and onions.
Drain off grease. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
May add water, if needed. Heat thoroughly.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Beat together until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.
Serves 10.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O with boiling water.
Cool Jell-O, then stir in cream cheese, mayonnaise and pineapple.
Chill in 9 x 12-inch pan or mold.

title: tomato soup french dressing
directions: Pour soup into blender.
Add other ingredients and blend until thoroughly mixed.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups dressing.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes
and
onions through food chopper. Add all other ingredients
and
boil
2 hours or until thick, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.
Pour into sterilized jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Put
on cap, screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: forget me nots
directions: In frying pan, brown beef and pork.
Add cheese, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted. Spread on bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until bubbly. May be prepared ahead and frozen before baking.
Serves 16.

title: linguine with turkey
directions: Cook linguine according to box directions.
Add the broccoli flowerets to the linguine 2 minutes before it is done cooking. When it is finished, drain linguine and broccoli together.
Keep hot.
Meanwhile, saute carrots and celery in margarine 3 minutes. Stir flour into sauteed carrots.
Add chicken broth and sage to vegetable mixture.
Stir in turkey meat until sauce comes to a simmer.
Simmer 1 minute.
Pour over warm pasta in serving bowl. Sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Serve immediately.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place into well-greased bread pan and bake for 1 hour.
Good for garlic toast.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix in bowl.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with a few cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef for sandwiches
directions: Slow cook the beef in a crock-pot or slow cooker in 1 1/2 cups water until it starts to fall apart.
Mix other ingredients and add to beef.
Continue to slow cook until beef is shredded.
Total cooking time: approximately 12 hours.
Serve on sub rolls.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop teaspoonfuls into hot grease.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch in double boiler until very thick, stirring constantly.
Turn off and add strawberry Jell-O. Set aside to cool.
Slice strawberries and sprinkle with sugar and put in refrigerator for a while.
Dip strawberries out of bowl with spoon with holes in it so as not to use the juice and fold strawberries in mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool and cover with whipped cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Heat a large iron skillet and pour half the mixture into it.
Layer beef, cheese, onions and peppers over mixture.
Pour the remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: acorn squash baked with pineapple(6 servings))
directions: Remove seeds and fiber from squash halves.
Place in greased baking dish and put 1 teaspoon each of sherry, brown sugar and butter in each half.
Cover and bake in a hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes or until tender.
Scoop cooked squash out of shells, leaving wall about 1/4-inch thick.
Mash squash and combine with the remaining 4 tablespoons butter, pineapple, salt and nutmeg. Beat until well blended.
Spoon back into shells and return to hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.

title: fruity frappe
directions: Place prepared drink mix, yogurt and fruit in blender container; cover.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: american beef and peppers
directions: Brown meat in oil in heavy skillet.
Add soup, water and seasonings.
Simmer covered over low heat about 20 minutes. Additional water may be added if needed to keep liquid the consistency of rich gravy.
Add pepper and onion rings to meat and continue cooking until tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cereal(cook by myself)
directions: If I mix cereals I use 1 1/2 cups of each - usually about 12. Then you eat it.

title: "grate" zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix wheat and white flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
In medium bowl, mix together egg, egg white, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir to combine; do not beat.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; let set until thickened, not set. Crush graham crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Press 2/3 over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and jello.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with rest of crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix corn and beans together and place in small greased casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour over corn and beans.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with 1 package (roll) of Ritz crackers (crushed).
Put on top of casserole and cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: curry-cajun spiced chicken
directions: Combine honey, water, mustard, butter, spices, lemon juice and garlic in a rectangular baking dish.
Add chicken breast halves, turning to coat each in mix.
Arrange in a single layer.

title: scrumptious shrimp
directions: In a microwave-safe pan, place all of the ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on the highest power for about 7 to 10 minutes.
When the shrimp are red and juicy they are ready to eat.
Can be served as an appetizer or as a side dish with any meal!

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Makes about 1/4 cup of dressing.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Put Snax mix and nuts in 9 x 13 casserole. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over all. Bake at 200° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread (press) cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Bake until cookie is done, approximately 15 to 18 minutes. Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice together.
Spread on top of cooled cookie dough.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.
Example:
Start in center and place a strawberry, then work outward with blueberries, kiwi, bananas, oranges, strawberry slices, etc.

title: cheerwine punch
directions: Mix Cheerwine and pineapple juice; chill.
Freeze some of the mixture and add along with ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand at the end. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Bake anytime thereafter.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with floured cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix well; add orange slices last.
Use the juice to mix cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: In a pan sprayed with nonstick spray, saute the turkey, celery, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; top with your choice of veggies.
Pour tomato sauce over this and top with cheese.
Cover with the crescent rolls. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until the crust is a golden brown.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.
Lo-cal.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 2 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt and add to egg mixture.
Add oleo, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Pour in greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt fanny's squash
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 stick butter and crumbs.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and pour on top of mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: mint salad
directions: Mix pineapple, juice, dry jello and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add mints and Cool Whip and serve or put in cupcake papers in muffin tins and freeze.

title: "baked chicken salad"(serves 6)
directions: Add lemon juice and onion juice to Miracle Whip; blend well. Pour over chicken, celery, almonds and pimiento mix.
Put into shallow pan.
Crush potato chips with grated cheese and sprinkle over the top of the chicken mixture.
Bake in medium oven, 350°, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through and bubbly.

title: indian brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, salt, cocoa, vanilla, sugar, flour and eggs until smooth.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover top with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven; bake until marshmallows are melted, or until done.
Cool completely; spread with frosting.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place sliced carrots in 1 1/2-quart pot.
Mix cornstarch in water until dissolved.
Add all ingredients to carrots and simmer until tender.
Turn heat up to medium-high until glaze thickens. Stir often to keep from sticking.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well coated.
Roll into bite sized balls.
Bake on butter flavored Pam-sprayed cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: scrabble party mix
directions: Grease a large roaster pan with Crisco.
Put oven on lowest temperature setting.
Leave in oven for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and box in tins or jars.

title: one dish potatoes
directions: Spread hash browns in large greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except corn flakes, and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes, enough to make a nice cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: With a mixer, combine first 5 ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in a 9 x 12 baking dish. Serve frozen. Keeps well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Melt margarine. Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Dip biscuit pieces, one by one, in margarine, then put it into the cinnamon-sugar mixture, then into a tube pan.
Continue until all the biscuit pieces are in the tube pan.
Pour any remaining margarine and cinnamon-sugar over biscuits.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Immediately flip.
Cool.
Pick off pieces and enjoy.

title: peach butter
directions: Make spice bag of 3 spices.
Put all in a large pot and cook until thickened.
Remove spice bag.
Put in jars and seal with paraffin.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Add butter. Mix well.
Cook on low heat in double boiler, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.
525 calories per slice but it sure is good.

title: mattie's mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar gradually.
When this is firm, fold in crushed Ritz crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with chocolate.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pineapple dessert easy
directions: Fold together, refrigerate few hours.
Top with cherry when serving (Comstock cherry filling).
Does not firm rapidly.

title: small cheese pies
directions: You will also need midget cupcake holders.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Melt and cool butter; pour over flour mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Serve hot or cold with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk until batter is soft.
Then add flavoring and beat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball with ham
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the parsley together well. Shape into a ball and roll in the chopped parsley.
Refrigerate until ready to serve with crackers.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: chicken glamorous
directions: Sprinkle rice in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; cover with dry onion soup.
Mix chicken soup with water.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over rice and onion soup.
Put chicken on top.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in remaining soup and water mixture.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar, vanilla and water and cream well. Add flour, salt and grated nuts; mix.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with vinegar, onion, celery, pickle, seasonings, mayonnaise and salad mustard.
Toss to blend.
Fold in eggs.
Chill.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Beat together until light and fluffy.
Fill 1/3 cup.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.
Cool on rack and top with filling.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine egg, oil and applesauce.
Blend remaining ingredients. Bake in a nonstick muffin pan for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: revolutionary comforts
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Drop mixture by tablespoons in hot oil or fat.
Cook through.
Drain on paper towel.
Dip in powdered sugar to coat while still warm.
Enjoy!

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with tines of fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on cake rack.
Serve at room temperature.
They freeze well.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Add sugar gradually, then oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef and cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with beef and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread.

title: blue punch
directions: Combine water and lemonade mix.
Add sherbet and coloring, blue and a little green.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Cook until onions clear and meat is done.
Pour off any excess fat.
Add 2 cans of tomato sauce and liquid off tomatoes.
Add seasonings and let simmer for 1 hour. Cook lasagne noodles.
Use an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Place in layers the noodles, meat sauce, slices of Mozzarella cheese, spread thin layer of Ricotta cheese, sprinkle with 1/2 can of chopped tomatoes and spread 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Repeat second layer and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, confectioners sugar, cracker crumbs, water and vanilla in bowl; mix well.
Shape into small balls; place on trays.
Chill overnight.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Slice roast into small thin slices.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Then remove and place roast into pressure kettle.
In a separate bowl mix the soup mix as directed on box.
Add more water, if needed.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with potatoes or other dishes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in baking dish.
Mix soups and butter in saucepan until butter melts.
Spread chestnuts on top of broccoli, then pour soups on top.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the box.
Drain the shrimp, keeping the liquid.
Combine macaroni, onions, celery and shrimp with mayonnaise.
Pour in part of the liquid retained and stir.
Chill before serving.

title: frost me not cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in pan over low heat.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla. Mix only until blended.
Do not beat.
Add chocolate and nut mixture and again stir carefully, not beating.
Pour into cupcake liners.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: mother's applesauce date cake
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and egg.
Blend dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture, applesauce, vanilla and dates to dry mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can be used as a coffee cake or as a dessert with whipped cream.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then alternate with flour and milk, a small amount at the time, until used up, beating well after each addition.
Then beat egg whites until they stand up in peaks and fold in batter.
(Don't beat.)

title: hamburger soup
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown, drain and cool sausage.
Trim and cube bread.
Line baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Put rice (both packages) in a large, flat casserole.
Pour chicken broth over it; dot with butter.
Add pepper and salt, then add mushrooms.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture and sprinkle onion soup over everything.
Dilute mushroom soup with a little water and spoon over each chicken breast.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
Bake covered 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add vinegar and mix.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add oil and mix thoroughly.
Baste as you cook chicken.

title: apple and yam casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine pie filling and potatoes in a buttered 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and green peppers, then put hamburger in frying pan with a little grease and brown.
Then add onions and green peppers. Sprinkle with garlic salt, oregano, celery salt, meat tenderizer, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and simmer, stirring together until onions and green peppers are done.
Then add 1 can of tomato sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
In the meantime, put 1 large can of tomatoes and 1 small can of tomatoes in a large pot and mash.
Spoon chili powder in and add kidney beans.
Stir thoroughly.
Now add ingredients from frying pan and cook for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat with all spices added.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix meat mixture and noodles, add spaghetti sauce.
Place in 9 x 13 pan.
Cover top with cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Cover, bake 350 for 35 minutes.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in glass casserole dish; set aside.
Combine milk, sugar and Bisquick; mix by hand. (Batter will be thin with tiny lumps.)
Pour into casserole dish over butter; do not stir again.
Pour fruit into the middle; make a circle with fruit using a knife.
Be careful not to touch bottom or sides with knife.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm for best flavor.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain grease.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick, about 1/2 hour, on medium to low heat.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips.
Pour over Crispix cereal.
Stir gently to coat (use spatula).
Pour 1/2 box of confectioners sugar in a brown bag; pour in cereal, then add remainder of confectioners sugar.
Close bag and shake to coat cereal.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine the chocolate chips and batter; cook and stir over low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix well.
Shape one tablespoonful (use measuring spoon) of dough around each candy kiss, covering completely. Place one inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for six to eight minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear shiny but become firm as they cool.
Do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Cook until tender.
Reserve 3/4 cup liquid.
Cream 1/2 cup shortening, sugar and egg until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and remaining ingredients.
Add liquid. Stir in raisins.
Pour into cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While warm, ice with confectioners sugar.

title: fried rice orientale
directions: Saute onions, meat and celery in the oil.
Add rice, soy sauce and seasoning to taste.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, refrigerate until chilled. Serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, spices and oil together, then add in order, the pumpkin, water, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Mix well.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: puto (steamed cupcake)
directions: Beat eggs with vanilla.
Stir in milk and water.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually beat into egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Steam for 10 to 15 minutes or until done (when inserted toothpick comes out dry).

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Using a whisk, mix condensed milk and cream cheese.
Add pineapple and oranges to mixture.
Mix with a mixer on low speed. Fold in cool whip and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining 2 eggs and cup of flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 225°.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Put cut up rhubarb in an unbaked pie shell. Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and water. Spread well over rhubarb. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
The cream filling forms in baking.

title: lima bean surprise
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz with cream of mushroom soup (warm just enough to melt).
Add other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish; top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with melted margarine and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together with hands.
Add flour, pepper, salt and Rice Krispies.
Roll in tiny balls and press flat with a fork after placing on a slightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let brown slightly to crisp.

title: meat pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix lightly, press mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
While meat shell is baking, make up mashed potatoes mixture, mixing in the cheese.
Remove meat shell from oven and drain off any fat.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Fill shell with potatoes and sprinkle top with parsley flakes.
Return to oven for another 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with mayonnaise until moist.
Add a few shrimp and some finely chopped parsley.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Refill egg white halves with mixture.
Top with 1 shrimp and small sprig of parsley; sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients. Form into 6 patties. Chill at least 2 hours. Fry in small amount of olive oil over medium heat until cooked through and brown on both sides.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice cooker jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in rice cooker.
Start cooker and stir at least once every 15 minutes to prevent sticking.
When the cooker is finished, let steam for 10 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Mix together, except chocolate and paraffin.
Make mixture into balls.
Dip in chocolate, then in paraffin.
Place on wax paper.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together with cream cheese, sugar, milk and peanut butter until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Serves 6.

title: happy cake
directions: Melt butter. Mix together with spoon.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and pierce skin of sweet potatoes.
Microwave on high for 6 - 8 minutes until almost tender.
Peel sweet potatoes and slice 1/8 inch thick.
Place in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Mix together brown sugar, marmalade and orange peel.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with a tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on high for 5 - 6 minutes or until heated well.
Stir half way through cooking.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Pour 2 cups sugar over cranberries; let set overnight.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Roll into a ball then cover with cocktail sauce.

title: allie's pie crust(for one crust)
directions: Add shortening and salt to flour in mixing bowl.
Cut with pastry blender until mixed to size of small pea.
Add cold water, a little at a time, and mix well until mixture forms a ball.
If more water is needed, sprinkle on a little at a time.
Lightly flour board and roll out for crust.

title: western salad(robbie 1977)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Fritos, adding them right before serving. Break up Fritos with rolling pin or hands while still in package. This makes a large bowl of salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together.
Spread in a large Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Layer chopped lettuce and tomatoes on top of that.
Refrigerate again for a few hours.
Serve with tortilla chips of your choice.

title: chicken noodle soup casserole
directions: Mix all but 1/2 cup bread crumbs for top.
Pour in 10 x 13 pan.
Put 1/2 cup bread crumbs on top.
Squeeze margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Salt and pepper fish fillets.
Melt margarine or butter in shallow baking dish in hot (400°) oven until brown.
This gives distinctive flavor.
Place fish, flesh side down, in sizzling hot margarine.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes; turn and baste with juice. Sprinkle with paprika and cheese.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
This is good for any fish fillets.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Peel potatoes and slice round slices.
Boil potatoes 10 minutes and drain.
In casserole dish, add hamburger, salt, pepper, onion powder and potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni according to box directions.
Add a little extra milk to make a little soupy.
Then mix in tuna and cream of mushroom soup.
Then add peas.
Mix.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 45 minutes.

title: di's spicey walnuts
directions: Pour mixture over nuts.
Toss to coat.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Eat as snack or add to tossed green salad.

title: hot mustard for dipping
directions: Combine dry mustard and vinegar, mixing well.
Cover with Saran.
Refrigerate overnight.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add mustard and vinegar mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix and put into bowl and cover and let set for 4 days.

title: deer jerky
directions: Prepare marinade in gallon glass jar.
Use lean meat.
Cut into 1/4 inch strips. Soak meat to remove blood.
Put meat in jar with marinade; mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 days.
Mix daily in the jar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in an oblong dish and cover with mixture of sour cream and soup.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Then sprinkle the peanuts on top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: herb butter
directions: Heat and serve over hot, cooked vegetables.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Mix 1
to
minutes
on
high heat, 2/3 cup cake mix, brown sugar, corn syrups, vanilla and 3 eggs.
Set aside.
Now mix rest of	cake
mix,
butter
and
last egg.
Mix until it becomes a crumbly
dough and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Pour first	mix over
baked
crust.
Sprinkle with pecans and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown hamburger, seasoned with salt and pepper, in a large skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Stir.
Place cabbage and green pepper over top.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split chili peppers lengthwise and remove seeds and pith. Spread chilies in a single layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, green onions and 1 1/2 cups of the Mozzarella cheese over chilies.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour and salt together until smooth.
Pour over chilies and cheese. Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Meanwhile, mix salsa with the remaining 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole and return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake.
Bake in 3 layer pans for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown beef with onions, drain.
Mix beef, pork and beans, brown sugar, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce in casserole dish.
Place bacon strips on top.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine.
Let set 12 hours.
Put in ice cream freezer.
Fill up to line with milk.
Freeze.

title: parmesan baked fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Rinse and pat dry.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Stir together reduced calorie mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, chives or green onions.
Spread mayo mixture over fillets and bake uncovered at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily, testing with fork.

title: wiggie's whimpies
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add peppers, onion and celery.
Saute until slightly tender.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for about 1 hour.
The longer it cooks the better it tastes.

title: tiger bites
directions: Melt chips for 2 minutes on high.
Mix cereal and nuts with melted chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill 15 minutes. Store at room temperature.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries and chop with oranges in food processor.
Mix with sugar, orange peel and rum.
Serve chilled.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit well.
Arrange in a casserole dish, except cherries.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and cinnamon; spoon over fruit. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and beat well. Add molasses to which you have added the soda. Mix cloves, ginger and cinnamon with flour. Add dry ingredients a little at a time to the sugar mixture. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Melt margarine, add flour and juice to make a white sauce. Add eggs, beat in.
Add sugar.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cook on low heat to thicken.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: double chocolate cream torte
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch round pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan. Invert onto serving platter.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Heat oil and flour to make paste.
Then add spices and liquids to make sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: bear roast
directions: Soak bear roast overnight in vinegar and water (1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water).
Parboil 1 hour and throw away liquid.
Add more water, onion, garlic (salt), potato, salt, pepper and 1 lid full of vinegar.
Bring to boil and cook until tender.
Bake for 1 hour, using some of broth from before.
Cover with foil until last 15 minutes; let brown.
Slice across the grain.

title: hobo pie
directions: Press meat in bottom of 3-quart pan.
Sprinkle milk over meat, add sliced potatoes, then sliced onions, then cubed cheese. Cover with mushroom soup, cover pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and milk and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add cubed cheese and broccoli.
Let simmer over low heat until dissolved.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put spices in bag. Mix sugar, lemon juice and orange juice together. Mix with apple cider. You can use apple juice.
Heat until hot.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix cheeses and chill while cooking 1 box of shells.
Brown hamburger and add spaghetti sauce.
Stuff shells with chilled cheese mixture.
Pour meat sauce over shells and top with extra Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy sesame chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Dip chicken in butter. Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Mix altogether.
(Should be very moist.)
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat the butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add flour and vanilla, mixing well after each addition. Roll out on a well floured surface, rolling dough thin.
Bake about 8 minutes in a 350° oven. Watch!
These brown very quickly.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground sirloin and onion.
Do not add Minute rice when browning meat.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt, pepper and sugar. Sprinkle flour over top.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Wash peppers; cut in half and remove seeds.
Drop into boiling water and boil 1 minute; drain. Stuff with meat mixture.
Top with buttered crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Do not cover.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey mustard pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloins on a rack coated with cooking spray.
Place rack in broiler pan and set aside.

title: meat balls
directions: Simmer chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice until smooth. Add salt.
Shape meat into small balls and drop into sauce.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Oh, so good!

title: kentucky wildcat cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.

title: mama's chocolate gravy
directions: Bring to boil, turn down heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pop off mushroom stems and chop.
In a large sauce pan brown ground beef, chopped mushroom stems, parsley, onions, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, and eggs.
Fill cavity of mushroom tops with meat mixture. Place in baking dish and bake at 450 degrees for approximately 15 minutes.

title: n h blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put the first six ingredients in a bowl (i.e. flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar).
Add oil, milk and eggs, mixing well after each one. Fold in the blueberries.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick after 45 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Bring oil and syrup to boil in skillet and add pecans.
Stir to coat.
Put on cookie sheet and bake 17 minutes at 325°.
Pour out on waxed paper and salt.

title: cough syrup
directions: Let boil.
Add a lump of butter.
Let melt and feed while warm.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off any grease. Add tomato sauce, taco seasoning and olives.
Separate rolls.
Arrange in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate and press together to make a crust (up the sides, too). Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips over the crust (dough), then add the meat mixture. Spread sour cream over meat.
Cover with cheese and sprinkle with remaining corn chips. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double cruncher cookie
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Combine shortening and sugars.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture and add other ingredients. Reserve 1/3 dough.
Shape remaining dough into balls using teaspoon.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass bottom dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape remaining dough into balls, using 1/2 amount for each ball as first time.
Flatten and bake as before.
Cool on wax paper.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil cleaned peppers in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Mix other ingredients; stuff peppers lightly. Stand upright in small baking dish. Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in covered container over night in refrigerator.

title: strawberry-rhubarb butter
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar in pan or bowl.
Let stand overnight. Cook slowly for about 15 minutes.
Take off heat.
Mix in Jell-O. Put in containers and store in refrigerator.

title: fresh apple cake with caramel glaze
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Combine flour, spices and soda.
Add to first mixture and beat well.
Add apples and pecans, mixing well. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions; stir until golden brown.
Add broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers.
Re-cover; simmer for 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture.
Stir until thickens or boils.
Add tomatoes; heat.
Serve over rice.

title: wassail
directions: Put spices in basket of large coffeepot with juice in bottom and perk, or put spices in cheesecloth and juice in a large pot. Bring just to boiling and simmer.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion, potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly until potatoes are very soft. Mash the potatoes with masher until fairly smooth.
Add milk; continue cooking until soup comes to a boil.
Add parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: grape salad
directions: Stir 2 packages lemon-flavored gelatin with 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly on a spoon.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a large size electric skillet.
Set control dial at 300°.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and blended.
Turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: egg custard
directions: Add vanilla to beaten eggs, then sugar by the teaspoon. Alternately with milk, keep mixing until all milk and sugar are added and sugar is dissolved.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use a 10-inch pie crust.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients; chill in refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with salt and pepper.
(Pour off excess grease.)
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Combine other ingredients less 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with rest of Mozzarella.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings each.

title: banana bread
directions: You will need 1 big bowl, 1 big wooden spoon, 1 fork, 1 bread pan (rub some cooking oil around the inside of it), 1 wire cooling rack, 1 measuring cup and 1 set of measuring spoons.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add thawed green peas and cooked potatoes to beef mixture.
Season with cumin and salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix well.
In large greased shallow casserole dish, pour small amount of enchilada sauce and spread over bottom of dish.
Place one tortilla shell at edge of dish; fill center of tortilla with about 2 to 3 tablespoons of beef mixture.
Roll tortilla, edges down.
Continue this method with remaining tortillas.
Pour enchilada sauce over enchiladas, covering as much tortilla as possible.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly and hot.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; save water.
Remove bones from chicken and put chicken back into water.
Add Mrs. Grass's soup mix (everything except noodles).
Add 1 stick margarine and some milk with cornstarch to thicken.
Cook until thickened.
Put into a greased baking pan.
Make Bisquick as for biscuits.
Drop onto chicken mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix milk, sour cream, soup, butter and 1 cup cheese in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Peel and slice potatoes and lay in dish.
Salt and pepper and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden butterscotch brownies
directions: Beat oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time and beat after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and add the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cornstarch pudding
directions: Melt baking chocolate in double boiler over simmering water and add milk.
Stir until well blended.
Combine together the sugar, cornstarch and salt and add a small amount of hot chocolate mixture, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 20 minutes longer. Add butter and vanilla.
Spoon into serving dishes and press waxed paper directly onto surface of pudding.
Cool and chill.
Serve with sweetened cream if desired.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian curried cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with dip size Fritos.
For a festive look, double the recipe and serve in hollowed out pineapple half.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 pan, layer tortillas, onion, soup and chicken. (This usually makes 3 layers.)
In top layer, add jalapenos. Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creamed beef on toast
directions: Brown beef in shortening slowly.
Sprinkle flour on top.
Mix well.
Pour milk on top.
Gently stir until thick.
Serve on toast points or potatoes, etc.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and butter, then add peanut butter.
Stir in over Crispix.
Put powdered sugar in bag; add Crispix and shake.

title: goop (frito pie)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add chili mix, Ro-Tel and Ranch Style beans.	Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese and half and half.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over corn chips.

title: ahin's specialty
directions: Fry
boneless
chicken with crushed garlic in oil, then slice cooked chicken into bite size pieces.
Slice lup chong; fry separately.
Combine
chicken
and lup chong with rest of ingredients,
except
green
onions.
Add
salt
and pepper to taste.
Mix and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.	Garnish with green onions.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Butter dish or baking pan.
Put all ingredients in dish or pan. Mix well and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg and salt; shape into 18 meatballs.
Brown in small amount of oil on all sides in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add water, rice, carrots, green pepper and onions.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add Velveeta.
Heat until Velveeta melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Place canned cherry pie filling in bottom of cake pan.
Pour this over cake mix and bake at 350°.
When done, invert on a platter immediately.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon
until almost crisp.
Add onion, green pepper and minced garlic.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar, soy sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes.
Add rice to mixture and bake in oven, covered, for 30 minutes or until done.
Stir after 15 minutes in oven.
Add water in small amounts if needed.
Test for doneness.

title: magnolia house chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
While chicken cooks, marinate mushrooms in lemon juice.
Add Madeira, sherry or broth to chicken in pan; turn over.
Simmer another 5 minutes, or until chicken breasts are cooked through (do not overcook).
Remove to warm platter.
Turn heat to high; boil liquid mixture down to about 1/4 cup.
Add mushrooms; saute until mushroom liquids are evaporated.
Add cream; boil over high heat until sauce is thickened and reduced.

title: dawn's enchilada casserole
directions: Cut up tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Layer bottom of oblong casserole dish; sprinkle cheese over layer.
Sprinkle with onion and a few tablespoons of sour cream.
Repeat layers until all tortillas and onion are used.
Add rest of sour cream and cheese. Pour enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine water and butter; bring to boil.
Add broccoli and simmer 5 minutes.
Add uncooked rice; cover pan and set aside 5 minutes.
Stir in undiluted soup and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: quick tuna dish
directions: Heat
tuna,
celery
soup
and water.
Serve over rice. Another
way to serve this dish is to pour over cooked noodles in casserole
dish.
Sprinkle
with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over bottom of pie crust.
Top with pecan pieces.
In small bowl combine brown sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Pour over pecans. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top is deep golden brown; cool.
Garnish with whipped cream and melted chocolate chips.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Roll graham crackers and mix with melted butter.
Put package butterscotch chips on graham crackers.
Layer package chocolate chips next.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over chips.
Sprinkle coconut.
Sprinkle pecans over.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easter cake(makes three 9-inch layers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 3 (9-inch) circles of wax paper to fit layer cake pans; grease pans.
Line bottom of pans with wax paper.
Then grease and flour paper.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Blend well; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Divide into pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add onion.
Combine beaten egg and buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat.
Cook until golden brown.
Hush puppies will float when done.
Drain on paper towels or brown paper bag.
Makes 35 to 40 small hush puppies.

title: cajun party mix
directions: Melt margarine in uncovered roasting pan in a 250° oven.
Stir in parsley, celery salt, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and Tabasco sauce. Add cereal. Stir until well coated. Bake for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Stir in onions.
Cool on paper towels. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: banana split cake(no bake)
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter and eggs no less than 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust and cover with sliced bananas, then spread 1 (No. 2) can pineapple and cover with large Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans and cut up cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash thin; cook for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place cheese in bottom of casserole dish.
Add salt, squash and pepper.
Add onion and green chilies; top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: classic beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch strips, about 1 1/2 inches long.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook and stir until onion is tender, then remove from skillet.

title: old fashioned  sweet potato pone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices into a bowl. Cream shortening, gradually beat in sugar and eggs. Add milk alternately with dry ingredients. Beat until smooth, add milk, mix well. Bake in greased pan 30 minutes or until done.

title: mock barbecue
directions: Brown onion and ground chuck.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remainder of ingredients and simmer until thick.
Serve hot on buns or open face on bread.

title: easy fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottom and sides of a 12-cup Bundt pan. In large bowl, cream butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and nuts until well blended. Pour batter into prepared pan. Cool completely.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown turkey and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer; mix well.
Place 1/2 sauce in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 1/2 noodles (dry) on sauce.
Add all of cottage cheese, rest of noodles and rest of sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: coconut ice cream dessert
directions: Combine margarine and crushed Ritz crackers.
Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine softened ice cream, instant coconut pudding and milk.
Beat well with mixer until well combined.
Pour over cracker base.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Freeze until set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole, mix together beans, soup, 3/4 can onions and bacon.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: chocolate chocolate chip bars
directions: Make cookie mix bars according to directions on box, except only keep in oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut candy lengthwise and place chocolate side down on top of bars after you have removed it from the oven.
Then put back in the oven for 10 minutes more.
Let cool, then cut in squares.

title: grandma's cranberry bread
directions: Sift together into a large bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add butter, cutting in until crumbly, then add egg, orange peel, orange juice, raisins and cranberries.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quick sausage zucchini stew
directions: Cook sausage; slice.
Add zucchini, onion, garlic and oregano. Cook until tender.
Add beans and tomato.
Cook 10 more minutes. Great with rye bread and butter.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add chicken; let boil for 15 minutes. Add celery; boil 5 more minutes.
Add salt and rice.
Reduce heat; simmer until rice softens.
Great boost for winter colds.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Parboil chicken, cool and cut into small pieces.
Line bottom of dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion.
Spread over chicken. Melt butter, crumble crackers and mix with butter and poppy seed. Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tender golden fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Add salt to taste.
Place flour in a paper bag.
Drop chicken into bag and shake well until all chicken is covered.
Place chicken into a skillet about 1 inch of oil (hot oil).
Cover skillet.
Turn heat down.
Cook until brown.
Turn and cook this side until brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: mixed fruit salad(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce leaves.
Toss gently to coat.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add all others.
Mix everything very well.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ceviche
directions: Finely chop cilantro, tomatoes, chilies (deveined and seeds removed) and white onion.
Add juice from all the lemons to chopped vegetables.
In a big bowl add vegetables, Spanish olives, cooked shrimp, both cans of V-8 juice and olive oil.
Chill for 2 hours.
Before serving, add avocados.
Great with saltine crackers.
Yields between 8 and 12 servings.
Preparation time: 45 minutes.

title: baked pasta primavera
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a large baking dish.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Toss with oil.
Spoon into large bowl.
Place broccoli in a large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook broccoli over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cool running water.
Add broccoli to pasta in bowl.

title: granola or granola salad
directions: Mix together and bake on large cookie sheet at 350°.
Stir occasionally to keep from scorching.
Remove from oven.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Break apart and add nuts, if desired.
Mix with Cool Whip to make salad.
Leave out Cool Whip to use as granola.

title: donna's baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot and simmer 2 hours.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
Pour hot sauce immediately into jars according to correct canning procedures.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: pear crunch
directions: Drain pears, reserving liquid.
In casserole, place each half of pear.
Sprinkle each with your crumb ingredients (combine brown sugar, cornflake crumbs, cinnamon and butter).
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Add liquid.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: meat and potato loaf
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain, reserving liquid.
Mash potatoes, adding about 3 tablespoons of the reserved liquid to make a stiff consistency.
Stir in parsley, thyme and marjoram.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Set potatoes aside.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat; beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Allow to cool slowly away from draft.
Cut off tops with sharp knife.
Scoop out soft dough.
Fill with cream or vanilla pudding.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix the rest of ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cut fat into flour.
