Beat the egg with sugar and add to the milk.
Add enough of this mixture to the flour to make a soft dough.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with large biscuit cutter. Brush each biscuit with fat and fold 1/2 over the other as for Parker House rolls.
Brush the tops with the remaining egg and milk mixture.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° to 425° about 15 minutes.

title: patches
directions: Peel the potatoes; grind or grate them and drain them in a colander.
Stir in the flour and milk to make a thin batter and add salt and pepper to taste.
Parsley and onions may be added. Fry them in a well-oiled, hot skillet.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer, blend butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with flour, 1/3 of milk at a time.
Blend well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then turn out.
When completely cool, frost. Makes two 9-inch rounds.

title: vegetable au gratin
directions: Cook vegetables; drain and cool.
Combine rest of ingredients, except bread crumbs and butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Brown bread crumbs in butter; sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until thick and bubbly.

title: pizza
directions: First you shape the dough, and then put the tomato sauce on the dough and then put the cheese on and finally put the sausage and hamburger on the top.

title: apple almond pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place pastry on lightly floured surface.
Using 9-inch cake pan as guide, cut 9-inch circle from pastry.
Cut scrap into decorative shapes for garnish, if desired. Place pastry and cutouts on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until puffed and golden.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: ginger beef marinade
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together except meat.
Pour over meat and refrigerate
up to five days.
Turn meat twice a day, broil or grill.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange stalks in greased casserole. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt the stick of butter.
Brown the onion in the butter.
Put the browned onion and drippings into a casserole dish.
Add beef consomme and 1 can of water.
Add rice.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: basic pastry
directions: Cut Crisco until flour and salt mixture; blend well.
Beat egg.
Add cold water, vinegar and vanilla.
Blend all ingredients together, mixing well. Makes 3 pie crusts.
This pastry freezes well.

title: mike's quick crab soup
directions: Combine all but the last 3 ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours.
Add special and claw crabmeats and Old Bay.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and drain.
In bowl, mix broccoli, mayo, 1/2 of the cheese and soup.
Put in buttered casserole dish, layering with cheese and crushed crackers.
Add 2 beaten eggs to top it.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits(like red lobster's)
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat with a wooden spoon for 30 seconds.
Drop dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown in 450° preheated oven.
Combine melted butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
Serve warm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear lettuce and spinach into bite size chunks and place in a large serving bowl. Add onion rings, thawed peas, chopped eggs, bacon and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle mixture with sugar, salt and pepper. Toss thoroughly.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges and add water to make 3 cups liquid.
Stir into puddings and cook 3 to 5 minutes until clear and thickened.
Add pineapple chunks, oranges and bananas while still hot.
Stir in cherries (well drained).
Chill overnight (the bananas stay white and firm).
Very festive if served in glass or crystal bowl.
Serve for Christmas brunch with Sausage and Egg Bake.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Wash and pick over blueberries.
Line 9-inch pie pan, using half the pastry.
Roll out remaining pastry for the top crust.

title: cheesecake
directions: Put in bottom of 8 to 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: merk's coffeecake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spread half of batter in a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lined on the bottom with wax paper.
Cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts and mix well.
Sprinkle one-half of this mixture evenly over batter in pan.
Cover with remaining batter. Sprinkle on remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: chunk style applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: toscana soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cook onion and bacon; crumble. Stir in garlic, chicken broth, water and potatoes. Bring to boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer 25 minutes until potatoes are tender. Stir in kale, whipping cream and sausage. Cook 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: addie's spinach casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Stir until smooth.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Blend sauce and remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: josephine's chicken roll-ups
directions: Thin cutlets and pound; salt and pepper.
In one bowl, mix sour cream and chives.
In another bowl put stuffing mix.
Spray a casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Dip cutlet into sour cream mixture to coat it good on both sides.
Then dip in stuffing mix on both sides.
Roll it up and line it up in the casserole pan.
Melt butter and drizzle across top of roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put lettuce, peas and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
One layer at a time, in order given, spread Miracle Whip on top.
Then put a layer of onion and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Crumble bacon or bits on top just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: paciullis' hot wings
directions: Melt Country Morning Blend.
Add all other ingredients; stir. Pour ingredients into a large flat container.
Set chicken wings into container.
Marinate overnight.
Arrange wings on a flat baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla flavoring with mixer until batter is fluffy.
Mix in flour until a dough is formed.
Teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In water from chicken cook spaghetti, add water if necessary. Melt oleo.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
To onion and pepper mixture, add mushrooms, pimento and Ro-Tel.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Mix ingredients and add to chicken and spaghetti.

title: arizona salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add the crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Let stand until just warm, then add marshmallows.
Let stand until firm.
Add 3 tablespoons salad dressing to a 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Stir and spread on top of jello and marshmallows, then cover top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Simmer vegetables and carrots together for a few minutes. Drain.
Add soup, diluted with milk.
Mix together and place in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake (light version)
directions: Coat three 9-inch round cake pans with cooking spray; sprinkle 2 teaspoons flour in pans and shake to coat.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, applesauce and oil and add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do Not Beat). Stir in banana, vanilla and pineapple.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks. Spread Light Cream Cheese Frosting on top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, vanilla, cocoa and milk. Let cook until smooth, approximately 5 minutes.
Pour into greased pan or Pyrex dish.
Let set until firm.

title: sandy stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes in a big pot.
Serve hot.
Enjoy all you want.
There's no fat!

title: crunchy waldorf salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Chill until serving time.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: bloody mary
directions: Combine ingredients; serve over ice.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain.
In casserole, crumble cornbread.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, onion, green peppers, salt, pepper and cheese.
Mix well.
Cover with enough milk to cover the top of the casserole.
Bake until set (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Top with more cheese and return to oven to melt.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie shell.
Bake until brown.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
Let cool. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Add to sauce.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken, drain and let cool.
Grind chicken, eggs, and pecans.
Mix together with celery, relish, salt, pepper and mayo. Chill 4 hours before serving.
Good with town house crackers.

title: potato soup with a texas flavor
directions: Cook potatoes 15 minutes; drain and set aside.
Saute onions and peppers in butter until soft.
Stir in ham, chiles, pepper and cayenne; cook 1 minute longer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour or a little longer at 350°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss lettuce, artichoke hearts, pimentos and onion or layer these four ingredients.
Cover with cheese.
Just before serving, mix vinegar and oil, pour over salad and toss.

title: bonbons
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Then add peanut butter and stir well until melted.
Add crumbs and powdered sugar and the rest of the ingredients.
Form into small balls right away.
Set aside.

title: sweet pickle rings(red pickles)
directions: Peel and core cucumbers (sliced 1/2-inch thick). Scrape out seeds (look like rings).
Mix solution of pickling lime and 5 quarts water (plus enough to cover cucumbers).
Let stand 24 hours (time is not critical, can stand longer).
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Be sure to use porcelain or glass container to set brine. Drain well.
Rinse and cover with vinegar, red food coloring, powdered alum and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 2 hours or a little longer. Drain and discard solution.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Mix
and roll into small balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.	A toothpick works well for dipping.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Prepare pumpkin pie mix per label.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix (all will not be covered).
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: cajun style beef jerky
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate 24 to 30 hours.
Dehydrate.

title: cocoa bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the butter, molasses and sugar in a bowl.
Pour in the boiling water and stir.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
When the mixture in the bowl is cool, add the dry ingredients, along with the eggs.
Stir until smooth.
Pour the batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan and bake for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Combine and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with sliced Velveeta cheese. Top with bacon. Cover for half of the cooking time.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 10 minutes and poke holes in cake with large fork.
Pour can of sweetened condensed milk over cake and spread until milk is soaked in.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle on baking bits.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In medium saucepan over medium heat, combine sugar, brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Bring to a boil. Stirring constantly, boil for 7 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow cream until well incorporated and melted. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until smooth. Spread in prepared pan. Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix and pour into two pie pans.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm in the center.
Makes own crust.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan (don't drain).
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple, then spread cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix. Add butter in thin pats or melt and pour over.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: over that
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put graham cracker crumbs over that.
Put chocolate chips over that.
Put coconut flakes over that.
Put chopped nuts over that.
Put Eagle Brand milk over that.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Coat a saucepan with vegetable spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender. Sprinkle flour and dry mustard over vegetables, tossing gently to coat.
Gradually stir in skim milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and next 3 ingredients; cool slightly.
Gently stir in crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Spoon 3/4 cup into each of 4 serving dishes; top each with 1 1/2 teaspoons crumbs.
Place dishes on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Garnish with lemon, if desired.

title: low calorie egg nog
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Makes 10 (4 ounce) servings.
Low cholesterol (4 grams) and 92 calories.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots and let cool.
In large bowl, place cooked carrots, sliced onion, sliced bell pepper.
Toss to mix.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate in refrigerator at least overnight.

title: pizza recipe
directions: Add to hamburger, onion and bacon, the pizza sauce.
Spread on bun.
Add grated American cheese. Bake until cheese melts.

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Dip bread and brown both sides.

title: shish kabob
directions: You will need 4 skewers for this recipe.

title: egg in a cloud
directions: Butter baking dish. Arrange Potato in mounds. Make a dent in the center. Put and Egg in each dent. Sprinkle with Parsley. Bake until Eggs are done at 400.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
(Cake will sink in the middle.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients except bananas.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Add nuts and bananas and stir thoroughly.
Grease loaf pan and bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until toothpick or knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.
Keeps very well in refrigerator or freezer.
Best eaten at room temperature with cream cheese or plain.

title: quick pizza
directions: Pour tomato sauce onto buns, toast or biscuits.
Top with vegetable pieces (onion, broccoli, carrots, green peppers, zucchini) and grated cheese.
Heat to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: basic french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: chili cheese logs
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine cheese with lemon juice, garlic powder and pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in nuts.
Shape into a roll about 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in mixture of chili powder and paprika.
These may be frozen.
Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and dry jello.
Add oil, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in strawberries, coconut and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 layers at 350°.
Test for doneness.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese.
Dissolve the gelatin in the 1/2 cup cold water.
Add gelatin and other ingredients.
Grease mold with a little mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until mold is set overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.
Serve with crackers.

title: sharon's potato soup
directions: Chop onions and saute for 1 hour.
Brown bacon until crisp; crumble.
Shred cheese and set aside.
Cube potatoes, boil and drain.
Add chicken broth to potatoes.
Add milk and onions.
Heat to boiling.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add bacon and cheese. Enjoy!

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Remove seeds from chilies.
Layer on top of margarine (or you can use chopped chilies).
Grate cheese and layer over chilies.
Beat eggs; mix in well milk, Bisquick mix, salt and sugar.
Pour over cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add the milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix and spread in baking pan.
Spread cherries (seeded) on top of the batter.
Sprinkle sugar over cherries.
Add the water over all.
Bake for 45 minutes in medium oven.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, ReaLime and a few drops of coloring.
Pour into pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken
breasts in the oil.
Remove and cut into small bite
sized
pieces.
Saute mushrooms, pepper and onions until tender-crisp.
Add creamed soups and blend.
Add chicken and blend well.
Just
before
serving,
stir
in sour cream. Serve over hot, cooked noodles.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Put 1/2 mixture into a warm greased black skillet. *Sprinkle with 1/2 grated cheese.
Pour rest of mixture over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oyster stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems out of mushrooms, leaving a niche for stuffing. Saute mushroom caps in 2 tablespoons butter; set aside.
Saute green onions, garlic and chopped stems of mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add oysters and cook until oysters curl.
Add breadcrumb-Parmesan cheese mixture, then bind with the beaten egg. Stuff mushroom caps.
Place piece of Cheddar cheese on top of each mushroom and put under broiler for browning.
Serves 6 (3 each).

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Stir flour, baking soda and cinnamon together. Add pumpkin, sugar and eggs. Mix well. Line a jelly roll pan with foil, shiny side down and the dull side facing up. Pour batter onto pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle a tea towel and the baked cake with confectioners sugar. Turn the cake onto the towel. Remove the pan and gently lift the foil from the cake bottom. Roll up the cake in the towel as for a jelly roll and cool for 2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine in a large pot until tender.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, bouillon cubes, salt, thyme and rosemary.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with potato masher.
(If you prefer, leave vegetables in chunks.)
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sawmill cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, salt and spices until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Add syrup alternately with meal and flour, beating well after each addition. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to mixture; mix well. Bake in well-greased loaf pan in moderate oven.

title: raw persimmon pudding
directions: Arrange in bowl in layers.
Chill well before serving.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, 1 cup at a time.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
May be frozen at this time.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven about 13 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
If frozen, cooking may take a few extra minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Stiffen with flour and roll into small balls with hands and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: scandinavian smorgasbord(makes 36 appetizers)
directions: Arrange party bread on a tray; spread each slice with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise and/or mustard.
Top with a small lettuce leaf.
Top with tuna, egg slices, shrimp, cucumber or steamed vegetables.
Garnish as desired.

title: red chili puree sauce
directions: Arrange chiles on large baking sheet and bake in a 300° oven until chiles smell toasted	(about 4 minutes).
Let cool; discard stems and seeds.

title: cow butter
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Beat with mixer.

title: savory cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Cut cone-shaped wedge out of cauliflower core.
Place cauliflower and water in microproof casserole.
Cook covered on High (maximum power) 9 minutes.
Turn over halfway; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt.
Spoon sauce over top of cauliflower.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Cook, uncovered, on 70 (Roast) 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
(Cooking time is 10 minutes.)

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat. Add diced onion and green pepper. Drain. Add taco seasoning and taco salsa; simmer. Brown pie crust for a few minutes. Pour mixture into pie crust. Add both cheeses (sprinkle on top). Put back in oven and bake 10 to 12 minutes, until cheese melts, at 350°.

title: diet peanut butter cake
directions: Place a strainer over a deep bowl. Spoon applesauce into strainer and set aside to drain 15 minutes. (Will have about 1/3 cup drained applesauce.) Discard liquid.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with chopped onion until done.
Add tomato sauce and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Place cheese slices over ground meat mixture, then arrange biscuits on top of cheese. Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: stewed cauliflower
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Dilute 1/2 can of tomato paste in two cups of water; add to browned onion.
Dissolve one beef bouillon cube in 1/4 cup of warm water.
Mix with onion and tomato paste.
In another pan, brown fresh cauliflower in a little olive oil.
Add to liquid mixture and simmer until it gets thick, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: potatoes casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in buttered 9 x 13 inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk together, then add melted chocolate chips.
Slowly add powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan; cool.

title: my mother's fried apples
directions: Slice apples.
Do not peel.
Put in hot skillet with small amount of grease.
Cook until tender.
Add sugar and cook until brown.
Then add water.
Cook until sugar and water makes a syrup.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Do not grease pan. Mix ingredients and pour over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Pour on top.
Pour 2/3 cup of boiling water over all.
Do not mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: antha's potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until cooked thoroughly.
Cut into chunks (with peel) into large casserole dish.
Add other ingredients (butter will melt from heat of the potatoes) and mash/mix together (consistency of mashed potatoes).
Top with more cheese and microwave 5 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla; add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Take teaspoon of dough and roll in hands.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Garnish with quartered cherries.
In 350° oven, bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, and pour in greased pan.
Bake at 300° or 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Mix together well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Prepare 1 package of stuffing mix; put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread diced chicken on top of stuffing.
Prepare second box of stuffing mix; put on top of chicken.
Add celery, onion and chicken broth.
Beat eggs, milk, mayo and salt.
Pour on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, put cream of mushroom soup on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cheese, olive and picante sauce.
Spread evenly on tortillas.
If ham is used, place on top of spread.
Roll tortillas and cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: chicken and green pea fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks until thick; add milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add chicken and peas.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook in a frying pan in hot fat. Drain on paper towel.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a 12 inch skillet, melt butter over medium or high heat. Add shrimp, garlic, pepper and salt. Cook for 3 minutes or until shrimp is no longer pink. Stirring frequently. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: orange bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Cream the margarine and sugar. Stir in the flour and orange juice; beat until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking dish.
Place the orange segments or marmalade on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Let bread cool in the pan for 5 minutes, then remove and slice.

title: old style pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan and lightly flour.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating all the time.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour mixture.
Add lemon juice and pour batter in greased pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Yields 16 servings.
One serving contains 3 fat, 147 calories, 84 mg sodium, 31 mg cholesterol, 59 m carb, 14 gm fat

title: cheesy broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Mix broccoli, cauliflower, soup, egg and cracker crumbs in casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese and microwave for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops from peppers; discard seeds and membranes. Rinse in cold water. Stand upright in 2 quart microproof casserole. Add water. Cover and place in oven. Cook on high, (100%) 2 minutes. Pause; remove from oven. Drain water from peppers; set aside. Crumble beef into 1 1/2 quart microproof bowl. Add onion; place in oven. Cook on high, (100%) 3 minutes. Pause; stir; cook on high, (100%) 2 minutes. Pause; remove from oven, drain. Stir in rice, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, parsley, garlic, salt, and pepper. Fill peppers with beef mixture, mounding on top. Return filled peppers to casserole. Top with remaining tomato sauce. Cover and place in oven. Cook on high, (100%) 11 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in apples and fill greased tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: 3 grain holiday rice
directions: Rinse wild and brown rice well.
Chop celery in 1/4-inch cubes.
Chop green onions and saute with garlic in oil.
Crush garlic with a fork.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Stir in celery, wild and brown rice, herbs, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and cook gently for 30 minutes.
Add white rice and cook an additional 30 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Chop nuts and add just before serving.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup each size) servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be light brown and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture into lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
When cool, break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: hearty breakfast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough into two rectangles; firmly press perforations together to seal.
Spread rectangles with preserves; top with ham and process cheese food.
Roll up each rectangle, starting at narrow end; seal edge.
Cut each roll into four slices.
Place, cut side down, in greased 8-inch pie plate or round cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: company stew
directions: Cut elephant up into bite size pieces.
This should take about 3 months.
Add brown gravy, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 weeks.
Serves 3,800 people.
If more company is expected, add a rabbit, but do so only if necessary since most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: baked quail
directions: You will need four 8 x 8-inch squares of heavy foil.

title: 4 layer cake
directions: Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pan.
Heat and eat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder for taste.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugars, butter and eggs.
Add flour, pumpkin, water, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour in four greased and floured 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fat-free apple loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together in order given.
Spray Pam in a Bundt cake pan.
Pour mixture into Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
Mix powdered sugar and skim milk and sprinkle over top of cooled cake.

title: surprise meringues
directions: In a mixing bowl beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved (about 5-8 minutes).
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on baking sheets.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pepperoncini beef
directions: Pat meat with seasonings.
Place in crock-pot and place peppers on top.
Cook 5 hours on high or 8 hours on low.
Pull meat apart and add 1/4 cup of pepper juice.
Cook on low for additional 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Freezes well.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and put in plain salt and water. Soak for 1 hour.
Remove from salt water and drain well.
Put in ice water for 1 1/2 hours, then drain well.
Combine the remaining ingredients; pour this over the squash mixture and bring to a boil. Cook until pepper changes color.
Pack in jars and seal.
This is good instead of a salad and is good on hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: charles patsell's salad
directions: Toss ingredients in a large bowl. (Can be done right in serving bowl.)

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell pepper.
Drain.
Melt cheese in microwave. Mix with Ro-Tel chilies. Add hamburger mixture and stir well. Add mushrooms.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Drain vegetables; add all ingredients together.
Simmer on low heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
May need to add a small amount of water or extra barbecue sauce, depending upon desired consistency.
(May substitute ground turkey for a low-fat stew.)

title: camel jockey's beans(w. w. w.)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook at medium temperature for approximately 1 to 2 hours until onion and pepper are tender.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter and sprinkle in crumbs.
Pour milk in evenly.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Loosely cover leftovers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, place on paper towels and press until barely moist.
Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Cover and chill several hours.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with raw vegetables or on crackers.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare 9 x 13-inch pan by greasing and flouring.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut into pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix melted oleo, softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and drop by spoonfuls onto unbaked cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: grands! eggs benedict
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Bake biscuits as directed on can. Four baked biscuits are needed for this recipe. Freeze remaining 4 baked biscuits in plastic freezer bag for a later use.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and sour cream in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring until it boils.
Continue to boil until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°) or until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water. Stir in salt and vanilla.
Pour hot candy mixture over walnuts in a mixing bowl.
Mix until walnuts are evenly coated.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.
Separate walnuts.
Allow to cool and set.
When dry, store in airtight container.

title: sherried doves
directions: Sprinkle doves with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet or heavy saucepan.
Place dove breasts in skillet; add sherry and garlic.
Cover and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove breasts and keep warm; reserve 2 cups pan drippings (add water, if necessary).

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix until well blended.
Then pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Very moist and good.
